nodes.name: Documentation
nodes.documentation: An entity for defining the definitions that govern the document and should include the year and type of definitions referenced, along with any relevant documentation (such as master agreement) and the date it was signed.

nodes.name: CommodityPricingDates
nodes.documentation: The dates on which prices are observed for the underlyer.

nodes.name: BusinessUnitReference
nodes.documentation: Reference to an organizational unit.

nodes.name: nationalisationOrInsolvency
nodes.documentation: Defines the consequences of nationalisation, insolvency and delisting events relating to the underlying.

nodes.name: returnType
nodes.documentation: The type of return associated with the equity swap.

nodes.name: PricingStructure
nodes.documentation: An abstract pricing structure base type. Used as a base for structures such as yield curves and volatility matrices.

nodes.name: quotationRateType
nodes.documentation: The specification of the type of quotation rate to be obtained from each cash settlement reference bank.

nodes.name: RequestTradeReferenceInformationUpdate
nodes.documentation: Defines the structure for a message requesting information updates to a trade. The trade reference information should contain at least one trade identifier that the recipient is aware of.

nodes.name: Notional
nodes.documentation: An type defining the notional amount or notional amount schedule associated with a swap stream. The notional schedule will be captured explicitly, specifying the dates that the notional changes and the outstanding notional amount that applies from that date. A parametric representation of the rules defining the notional step schedule can optionally be included.

nodes.name: CommodityHub
nodes.documentation: A type defining a hub or other reference for a physically settled commodity trade.

nodes.name: ElectricityTransmissionContingencyType
nodes.documentation: The type of transmission contingency, i.e. what portion of the transmission the delivery obligations are applicable.

nodes.name: FrequencyTypeEnum
nodes.documentation: The schedule frequency type

nodes.name: Asset
nodes.documentation: Abstract base class for all underlying assets.

nodes.name: CompoundingMethodEnum
nodes.documentation: The compounding calculation method

nodes.name: BondOption
nodes.documentation: A Bond Option

nodes.name: maximumStockLoanRate
nodes.documentation: A type defining a percentage specified as decimal from 0 to 1. A percentage of 5% would be represented as 0.05.

nodes.name: SequencedDisruptionFallback
nodes.documentation: A Disruption Fallback with the sequence in which it should be applied relative to other Disruption Fallbacks.

nodes.name: Step
nodes.documentation: A type defining a step date and step value pair. This step definitions are used to define varying rate or amount schedules, e.g. a notional amortization or a step-up coupon schedule.

nodes.name: CreditSeniority
nodes.documentation: The repayment precedence of a debt instrument.

nodes.name: ReportingCurrencyType
nodes.documentation: A scheme identifying the type of currency that was used to report the value of an asset. For example, this could contain values like SettlementCurrency, QuoteCurrency, UnitCurrency, etc.

nodes.name: ElectricityProductTypeEnum
nodes.documentation: The type of electricity product.

nodes.name: FeaturePayment
nodes.documentation: Payment made following trigger occurence.

nodes.name: SettlementPriceDefaultElection
nodes.documentation: Coding scheme that specifies the settlement price default election.

nodes.name: DisruptionFallback
nodes.documentation: A Disruption Fallback.

nodes.name: ExchangeTradedCalculatedPrice
nodes.documentation: Abstract base class for all exchange traded financial products with a price which is calculated from exchange traded constituents.

nodes.name: CommodityPhysicalEuropeanExercise
nodes.documentation: The parameters for defining the expiration date(s) and time(s) for a European style option.

nodes.name: SettlementRateOption
nodes.documentation: A type defining the settlement rate options through a scheme reflecting the terms of the Annex A to the 1998 FX and Currency Option Definitions.

nodes.name: PositiveMoney
nodes.documentation: A type defining a positive money amount

nodes.name: DividendPeriodPayment
nodes.documentation: A time bounded dividend period, with fixed strike and a dividend payment date per period.

nodes.name: BullionTypeEnum
nodes.documentation: Defines which type of bullion is applicable for a Bullion Transaction.

nodes.name: PartyTradeIdentifiers
nodes.documentation: A type containing multiple partyTradeIdentifier.

nodes.name: CommoditySwap
nodes.documentation: Commodity Swap.

nodes.name: touchCondition
nodes.documentation: The specification of, for American-style digitals, whether the trigger level must be touched or not touched.

nodes.name: NationalisationOrInsolvencyOrDelistingEventEnum
nodes.documentation: Defines the consequences of nationalisation, insolvency and delisting events relating to the underlying.

nodes.name: ForecastRateIndex
nodes.documentation: A type defining a rate index.

nodes.name: ExtraordinaryEvents
nodes.documentation: Where the underlying is shares, defines market events affecting the issuer of those shares that may require the terms of the transaction to be adjusted.

nodes.name: Lien
nodes.documentation: A type describing the liens associated with a loan facility.

nodes.name: CalculationPeriodsReference
nodes.documentation: A pointer style reference to a calculation periods schedule defined elsewhere - note that this schedule consists of a series of actual dates in a calculationPeriods container.

nodes.name: PhysicalSettlement
nodes.documentation: A structure that describes how an option settles into a physical trade.

nodes.name: CommodityNotionalQuantitySchedule
nodes.documentation: The Notional Quantity per Calculation Period. There must be a Notional Quantity step specified for each Calculation Period, regardless of whether the Notional Quantity changes or remains the same between periods.

nodes.name: BusinessCentersReference
nodes.documentation: A pointer style reference to a set of business day calendar defined elsewhere in the document.

nodes.name: PaymentRule
nodes.documentation: The abstract base type from which all calculation rules of the independent amount must be derived.

nodes.name: GasDeliveryPoint
nodes.documentation: A scheme identifying the types of the Delivery Point for a physically settled gas trade.

nodes.name: PositionHistory
nodes.documentation: A list of events that have affected a position.

nodes.name: CommodityPremium
nodes.documentation: The commodity option premium payable by the buyer to the seller.

nodes.name: CalculationPeriodFrequency
nodes.documentation: A type defining the frequency at which calculation period end dates occur within the regular part of the calculation period schedule and thier roll date convention. In case the calculation frequency is of value T (term), the period is defined by the swap\swapStream\calculationPerioDates\effectiveDate and the swap\swapStream\calculationPerioDates\terminationDate.

nodes.name: ExecutionAdvice
nodes.documentation: A message advising a third party that a trade execution has occurred.

nodes.name: CommodityPipelineCycle
nodes.documentation: The pipeline cycle during which the physical commodity will be delivered.

nodes.name: ServiceProcessingStep
nodes.documentation: A type that can be used to describe what stage of processing a service is in. For example, Netting or Valuation.

nodes.name: LegalEntity
nodes.documentation: A type defining a legal entity.

nodes.name: DeterminationMethod
nodes.documentation: Coding scheme that specifies the method according to which an amount or a date is determined.

nodes.name: PartyId
nodes.documentation: The data type used for party identifiers.

nodes.name: DualCurrencyStrikePrice
nodes.documentation: A type that describes the rate of exchange at which the embedded option in a Dual Currency Deposit has been struck.

nodes.name: shareForOther
nodes.documentation: Defines the consequences of extraordinary events relating to the underlying.

nodes.name: fraDiscounting
nodes.documentation: The method of FRA discounting, if any, that will apply.

nodes.name: PremiumTypeEnum
nodes.documentation: Premium Type for Forward Start Equity Option

nodes.name: VarianceAmount
nodes.documentation: Calculation of a Variance Amount.

nodes.name: FormulaTerm
nodes.documentation: A type defining a term of the formula. Its value is the product of the its coefficient and the referenced partial derivatives.

nodes.name: DeclearReason
nodes.documentation: A type that describes why a trade was removed from clearing.

nodes.name: CommodityFx
nodes.documentation: A type defining the FX observations to be used to convert the observed Commodity Reference Price to the Settlement Currency. The rate source must be specified. Additionally, a time for the spot price to be observed on that source may be specified, or else an averaging schedule for trades priced using an average FX rate.

nodes.name: EquityOption
nodes.documentation: A type for defining equity options.

nodes.name: dividendPeriod
nodes.documentation: Defines the First Period or the Second Period, as specified in the 2002 ISDA Equity Derivatives Definitions.

nodes.name: WeightedAveragingObservation
nodes.documentation: A single weighted averaging observation.

nodes.name: Valuation
nodes.documentation: A structure that holds a set of measures about an asset, including possibly their sensitivities.

nodes.name: notionalAdjustments
nodes.documentation: The conditions that govern the adjustment to the number of units of the equity swap.

nodes.name: lengthUnit
nodes.documentation: Used for indicating the length unit in the Resource type.

nodes.name: calendarSource
nodes.documentation: Describes the date source calendar for a contract whereby the prices are from the underlying commodity price source (e.g. exchange traded futures contract), but the dates are based off another calendar (e.g. the listed option on the futures contract).

nodes.name: CollateralValueAllocationEnum
nodes.documentation: Denotes the method of collateral value allocation

nodes.name: MetalDelivery
nodes.documentation: The physical delivery conditions for the transaction.

nodes.name: FinalCalculationPeriodDateAdjustment
nodes.documentation: A type to define business date convention adjustment to final payment period per leg.

nodes.name: MetalTitleEnum
nodes.documentation: Describes how and when title to the commodity transfers.

nodes.name: ManualExercise
nodes.documentation: A type defining manual exercise, i.e. that the option buyer counterparty must give notice to the option seller of exercise.

nodes.name: BusinessDayConventionEnum
nodes.documentation: The convention for adjusting any relevant date if it would otherwise fall on a day that is not a valid business day. Note that FRN is included here as a type of business day convention although it does not strictly fall within ISDA's definition of a Business Day Convention and does not conform to the simple definition given above.

nodes.name: ElectricityDeliveryPoint
nodes.documentation: A scheme identifying the types of the Delivery Point for a physically settled electricity trade.

nodes.name: ServiceStatus
nodes.documentation: A type that can be used to describe the availability or other state of a service, e.g. Available, Unavaialble.

nodes.name: ReferencePool
nodes.documentation: This type contains all the reference pool items to define the reference entity and reference obligation(s) in the basket.

nodes.name: latestExerciseTimeType
nodes.documentation: Defines points in the day when equity option exercise and valuation can occur.

nodes.name: shareForShare
nodes.documentation: Defines the consequences of extraordinary events relating to the underlying.

nodes.name: ReturnSwap
nodes.documentation: A type describing return swaps including return swaps (long form), total return swaps, and variance swaps.

nodes.name: ReferenceAmount
nodes.documentation: Specifies the reference amount using a scheme.

nodes.name: Frequency
nodes.documentation: A type defining the frequency at which calculation period end dates occur within the regular part of the calculation period schedule and thier roll date convention. In case the calculation frequency is of value T (term), the period is defined by the swap\swapStream\calculationPerioDates\effectiveDate and the swap\swapStream\calculationPerioDates\terminationDate.

nodes.name: OilPipelineDelivery
nodes.documentation: The physical delivery conditions specific to an oil product delivered by pipeline.

nodes.name: Underlyer
nodes.documentation: A type describing the whole set of possible underlyers: single underlyers or multiple underlyers, each of these having either security or index components.

nodes.name: SpreadScheduleType
nodes.documentation: Defines a Spread Type Scheme to identify a long or short spread value.

nodes.name: ContactInformation
nodes.documentation: A type that represents how to contact an individual or organization.

nodes.name: IndexChange
nodes.documentation: A structure describing the effect of a change to an index.

nodes.name: RequestConfirmation
nodes.documentation: A message type defining the start of the confirmation process. The message may be used to request the confirmation of a new trade or any other event supported by FpML such as novation, terminations, amendments, etc.

nodes.name: AdditionalData
nodes.documentation: Provides extra information not represented in the model that may be useful in processing the message i.e. diagnosing the reason for failure.

nodes.name: EEPParameters
nodes.documentation: Excess Emission Penalty related parameters.

nodes.name: FormulaComponent
nodes.documentation: Elements describing the components of the formula. The name attribute points to a value used in the math element. The href attribute points to a numeric value defined elsewhere in the document that is used by the formula component.

nodes.name: AllocationApproved
nodes.documentation: A message indicating that a request to allocate a trade has been approved by the sender.

nodes.name: CalculationPeriodAmount
nodes.documentation: A type defining the parameters used in the calculation of fixed or floating rate calculation period amounts or for specifying a known calculation period amount or known amount schedule.

nodes.name: CommodityFixedPriceSchedule
nodes.documentation: The Fixed Price for a given Calculation Period during the life of the trade. There must be a Fixed Price step specified for each Calculation Period, regardless of whether the Fixed Price changes or remains the same between periods.

nodes.name: DifferenceTypeEnum
nodes.documentation: The ISDA defined value indicating the nature of a difference.

nodes.name: CoalProductType
nodes.documentation: A scheme identifying the types of coal for a physically settled coal trade.

nodes.name: TradeNovationContent
nodes.documentation: A structure describing a novation.

nodes.name: EEPRiskPeriod
nodes.documentation: TBD.

nodes.name: ConfirmationAgreed
nodes.documentation: A message indicating that a confirmation has been agreed by a counterparty.

nodes.name: NotionalAmount
nodes.documentation: A complex type to specify the notional amount.

nodes.name: Fra
nodes.documentation: A type defining a Forward Rate Agreement (FRA) product.

nodes.name: CorrectableRequestMessage
nodes.documentation: A type defining the content model for a request message that can be subsequently corrected or retracted.

nodes.name: PartyReference
nodes.documentation: Reference to a party.

nodes.name: PriceSourceDisruption
nodes.documentation: A type defining the parameters used to get a price quote to replace the settlement rate option that is disrupted.

nodes.name: DayOfWeekEnum
nodes.documentation: A day of the seven-day week.

nodes.name: Correlation
nodes.documentation: A type describing the correlation amount of a correlation swap.

nodes.name: Token60
nodes.documentation: A type defining a token of length between 1 and 60 characters inclusive.

nodes.name: ValuationSet
nodes.documentation: A set of valuation inputs and results. This structure can be used for requesting valuations, or for reporting them. In general, the request fills in fewer elements.

nodes.name: IdentifiedCurrency
nodes.documentation: Specifies Currency with ID attribute.

nodes.name: Metal
nodes.documentation: A type defining the characteristics of the metal product being traded in a physically settled metal transaction.

nodes.name: GasPhysicalQuantity
nodes.documentation: The quantity of gas to be delivered.

nodes.name: payRelativeTo
nodes.documentation: The Commodity specification of whether payments occur relative e.g. to the Trade Date, or the end of the month, etc.

nodes.name: ContractualTermsSupplement
nodes.documentation: A contractual supplement (such as those published by ISDA) and its publication date that will apply to the trade.

nodes.name: FxRateSet
nodes.documentation: A collection of spot FX rates used in pricing.

nodes.name: PricingParameterDerivative
nodes.documentation: A definition of the mathematical derivative with respect to a specific pricing parameter.

nodes.name: NettedSwapBase
nodes.documentation: A Variance Swap.

nodes.name: PricingMethod
nodes.documentation: For an asset (e.g. a reference/benchmark asset), the pricing structure used to price it. Used, for example, to specify that the rateIndex "USD-LIBOR-Telerate" with term = 6M is priced using the "USD-LIBOR-Close" curve.

nodes.name: TriggerConditionEnum
nodes.documentation: The specification of whether a payout will occur on an option depending upon whether the spot rate is above or below the trigger rate.

nodes.name: PricingParameterShift
nodes.documentation: A definition of a shift with respect to a specific pricing parameter.

nodes.name: loadType
nodes.documentation: LoadType is a summary of the full description of the settlement periods with respect to the region. Used for describing Electricity delivery schedules.

nodes.name: BrokerConfirmationType
nodes.documentation: Identifies the market sector in which the trade has been arranged.

nodes.name: DirectionalLegUnderlyer
nodes.documentation: A type describing return which is driven by a Variance Calculation.

nodes.name: OptionTypeEnum
nodes.documentation: Specifies the type of the option.

nodes.name: CommoditySettlementPeriodsPriceSchedule
nodes.documentation: The fixed price schedule for electricity that applies to one or more groups of Settlement Periods.

nodes.name: PartyTradeIdentifierReference
nodes.documentation: A reference to a partyTradeIdentifier object.

nodes.name: Person
nodes.documentation: A type that represents information about a person connected with a trade or business process.

nodes.name: EquityCorporateEvents
nodes.documentation: A type for defining the merger events and their treatment.

nodes.name: PhysicalForwardLeg
nodes.documentation: Physically settled leg of a physically settled Bullion Transaction.

nodes.name: SpecifiedPriceEnum
nodes.documentation: The Specified Price in respect of a Transaction and a Commodity Reference Price.

nodes.name: InstrumentId
nodes.documentation: A short form unique identifier for a security.

nodes.name: upperStrikeNumberOfOptions
nodes.documentation: A type defining a number specified as positive decimal greater than 0 exclusive.

nodes.name: ConfirmationMethod
nodes.documentation: A type used to represent the type of mechanism that can be used to confirm a trade.

nodes.name: CalculationFromObservation
nodes.documentation: Abstract base class for all calculation from observed values.

nodes.name: AdjustableOrRelativeDate
nodes.documentation: A type giving the choice between defining a date as an explicit date together with applicable adjustments or as relative to some other (anchor) date.

nodes.name: EquityBermudaExercise
nodes.documentation: A type for defining exercise procedures associated with a Bermuda style exercise of an equity option. The term Bermuda is adopted in FpML for consistency with the ISDA Definitions.

nodes.name: NonPeriodicFixedPriceLeg
nodes.documentation: The details of a fixed payment. Can be used for a forward transaction or as the base for a more complex fixed leg component such as the fixed leg of a swap.

nodes.name: FloatingRateCalculationReference
nodes.documentation: Reference to a floating rate calculation of interest calculation component.

nodes.name: DenominatorTerm
nodes.documentation: The type defining a denominator term of the formula. Its value is (sum of weighted partials) ^ power.

nodes.name: DeterminationMethodReference
nodes.documentation: A reference to the return swap notional determination method.

nodes.name: IndexAdjustmentEvents
nodes.documentation: Defines the specification of the consequences of Index Events as defined by the 2002 ISDA Equity Derivatives Definitions.

nodes.name: PaymentDetails
nodes.documentation: Details on the referenced payment. e.g. Its cashflow components, settlement details.

nodes.name: DateRange
nodes.documentation: A type defining a range of contiguous business days by defining an unadjusted first date, an unadjusted last date and a business day convention and business centers for adjusting the first and last dates if they would otherwise fall on a non business day in the specified business centers. The days between the first and last date must also be good business days in the specified centers to be counted in the range.

nodes.name: SettlementPeriodsStep
nodes.documentation: A reference to the range of Settlement Periods that applies to a given period of a transaction.

nodes.name: optionEntitlement
nodes.documentation: A type defining a number specified as positive decimal greater than 0 exclusive.

nodes.name: ClearingConfirmed
nodes.documentation: A message indicating that a clearing request has been acted on and as a result a trade has been cleared.

nodes.name: EventStatus
nodes.documentation: A coding scheme used to describe the matching/confirmation status of a trade, post-trade event, position, or cash flows.

nodes.name: ReportIdentification
nodes.documentation: A type that allows the specific report and section to be identified.

nodes.name: DataProvider
nodes.documentation: Specify as applicable. Parties may wish to refer to the state meteorological authority in a particular location or to an exchange or other third party data provider. Parties may find the definitions in the Commodity Definitions useful as a means of identifying potential Data Providers.

nodes.name: SwaptionAdjustedDates
nodes.documentation: A type describing the adjusted dates associated with swaption exercise and settlement.

nodes.name: Cashflows
nodes.documentation: A type defining the cashflow representation of a swap trade.

nodes.name: RequestedWithdrawalAction
nodes.documentation: A type that describes what the requester would like to see done to implement the withdrawal, e.g. ExpungeRecords, RetainRecords.

nodes.name: DefaultProbabilityCurve
nodes.documentation: A set of default probabilities.

nodes.name: QuotationSideEnum
nodes.documentation: The side from which perspective a value is quoted.

nodes.name: Unit
nodes.documentation: A type used to record information about a unit, subdivision, desk, or other similar business entity.

nodes.name: EarlyTerminationEvent
nodes.documentation: A type to define the adjusted dates associated with an early termination provision.

nodes.name: EnvironmentalProduct
nodes.documentation: A type defining the characteristics of the environmental product being traded in a physically settled environmental transaction.

nodes.name: RequestConsentRetracted
nodes.documentation: A message withdrawing a request that the sender be authorized by the recipient to peform an action.

nodes.name: Option
nodes.documentation: A complex type to support the credit default swap option.

nodes.name: PricingStructureValuation
nodes.documentation: An abstract pricing structure valuation base type. Used as a base for values of pricing structures such as yield curves and volatility matrices. Derived from the "Valuation" type.

nodes.name: BondReference
nodes.documentation: A type including a reference to a bond to support the representation of an asset swap or Condition Precedent Bond.

nodes.name: SettlementProvision
nodes.documentation: A type defining the specification of settlement terms, occuring when the settlement currency is different to the notional currency of the trade.

nodes.name: DiscountingTypeEnum
nodes.documentation: The method of calculating discounted payment amounts

nodes.name: IndexReferenceInformation
nodes.documentation: A type defining a Credit Default Swap Index.

nodes.name: OptionFeature
nodes.documentation: A type for defining option features.

nodes.name: WeatherLegCalculation
nodes.documentation: A type to capture details relevant to the calculation of the Payment Amount on a Weather Index Transaction.

nodes.name: MessageHeader
nodes.documentation: A type defining the content model for an exception message header.

nodes.name: OilTransferDelivery
nodes.documentation: The physical delivery conditions specific to an oil product delivered by title transfer.

nodes.name: ResetDatesReference
nodes.documentation: Reference to a reset dates component.

nodes.name: AllocationReportingStatus
nodes.documentation: Code that describes what type of allocation applies to the trade. Options include Unallocated, PreAllocation, PostAllocation.

nodes.name: PositiveAmountSchedule
nodes.documentation: A type defining a currency amount or a currency amount schedule.

nodes.name: RealisedVarianceMethodEnum
nodes.documentation: The contract specifies whether which price must satisfy the boundary condition.

nodes.name: CalculationPeriodsDatesReference
nodes.documentation: A pointer style reference to single-day-duration calculation periods defined elsewhere - note that this schedule consists of a parameterised schedule in a calculationPeriodsSchedule container.

nodes.name: ImpliedTrade
nodes.documentation: A type defining a type of trade that is implied by a post-trade event such as a novation. For example, if a novation moves $5mm in notional of an existing trade to a new party, there is an implied trade of $5mm at off-market terms. The fee represents the amoun by which the trade is off market. This even is used, for example in novations, where the implied trade and the corresponding fee must be segregated from the original or new trades for data access reasons (e.g. where the remaining party is not permitted to know the amount of a novation fee).

nodes.name: Basket
nodes.documentation: A type describing the underlyer features of a basket swap. Each of the basket constituents are described through an embedded component, the basketConstituentsType.

nodes.name: AdjustedRelativeDateOffset
nodes.documentation: A type defining a date (referred to as the derived date) as a relative offset from another date (referred to as the anchor date) plus optional date adjustments.

nodes.name: OilPhysicalLeg
nodes.documentation: Physically settled leg of a physically settled oil product transaction.

nodes.name: AdjustableRelativeOrPeriodicDates2
nodes.documentation: A type giving the choice between defining a series of dates as an explicit list of dates together with applicable adjustments, or as relative to some other series of (anchor) dates, or as a set of factors to specify periodic occurences.

nodes.name: disruptionFallbacks
nodes.documentation: The specification of how disruption fallbacks will be represented.

nodes.name: EventProposedMatch
nodes.documentation: A structure that describes a proposed match between trades or post-trade event reports.

nodes.name: FxLinkedNotionalSchedule
nodes.documentation: A type to describe a notional schedule where each notional that applies to a calculation period is calculated with reference to a notional amount or notional amount schedule in a different currency by means of a spot currency exchange rate which is normally observed at the beginning of each period.

nodes.name: BestFitTrade
nodes.documentation: A type used to record the differences between the current trade and another indicated trade.

nodes.name: QueryParameterId
nodes.documentation: A type representing an identifier for a parameter describing a query portfolio. An identifier can be anything from a product name like swap to a termination date.

nodes.name: EquityOptionTermination
nodes.documentation: A type for defining Equity Option Termination.

nodes.name: WeatherStation
nodes.documentation: Weather Station.

nodes.name: OilProduct
nodes.documentation: The specification of the oil product to be delivered.

nodes.name: CashSettlementPaymentDate
nodes.documentation: A type defining the cash settlement payment date(s) as either a set of explicit dates, together with applicable adjustments, or as a date relative to some other (anchor) date, or as any date in a range of contiguous business days.

nodes.name: AdditionalDisruptionEvents
nodes.documentation: A type for defining ISDA 2002 Equity Derivative Additional Disruption Events.

nodes.name: triggerCondition
nodes.documentation: The specification of whether a payout will occur on an option depending upon whether the spot rate is above or below the trigger rate.

nodes.name: OrganizationType
nodes.documentation: A code that describes what type of role an organization plays, for example a SwapsDealer, a Major Swaps Participant, or Other

nodes.name: DateReference
nodes.documentation: Reference to an identified date or a complex date structure.

nodes.name: Message
nodes.documentation: A type refining the generic message content model to make it specific to response messages.

nodes.name: ContractIdentifier
nodes.documentation: A type defining a contract identifier issued by the indicated party.

nodes.name: ReportingPurpose
nodes.documentation: A value that explains the reason or purpose that information is being reported. Examples might include RealTimePublic reporting, PrimaryEconomicTerms reporting, Confirmation reporting, or Snapshot reporting.

nodes.name: ExtensionEvent
nodes.documentation: A type to define the adjusted dates associated with an individual extension event.

nodes.name: DeClear
nodes.documentation: A structure describing an de-clear event.

nodes.name: unadjustedVarianceCap
nodes.documentation: A type defining a number specified as positive decimal greater than 0 exclusive.

nodes.name: Bond
nodes.documentation: An exchange traded bond.

nodes.name: RoutingIds
nodes.documentation: A type that provides for identifying a party involved in the routing of a payment by means of one or more standard identification codes. For example, both a SWIFT BIC code and a national bank identifier may be required.

nodes.name: PercentageTolerance
nodes.documentation: The acceptable tolerance in the delivered quantity of a physical commodity product in terms of a percentage of the agreed delivery quantity.

nodes.name: AdjustableOrAdjustedDate
nodes.documentation: A type for defining a date that shall be subject to adjustment if it would otherwise fall on a day that is not a business day in the specified business centers, together with the convention for adjusting the date.

nodes.name: ElectricityDeliveryPeriods
nodes.documentation: The different options for specifying the Delivery Periods for a physically settled electricity trade.

nodes.name: WeatherLeg
nodes.documentation: Weather Leg of a Commodity Swap defines Weather Index Swap transactions. Weather Index Swap transactions are OTC derivative transactions which settle financially based on an index calculated from observations of temperature and precipitation at weather stations throughout the world. Sub-Annex C of the 2005 ISDA Commodity Definitions provides definitions and terms for a number of types of weather indices. These indices include: HDD (heating degree days), CDD (cooling degree days), CPD (critical precipitation days). Weather Index Swap transactions result in a cash flow to one of the two counterparties each Calculation Period depending on the relationship between the Settlement Level and the Weather Index Level.

nodes.name: ProblemLocation
nodes.documentation: Provides a lexical location (i.e. a line number and character for bad XML) or an XPath location (i.e. place to identify the bad location for valid XML).

nodes.name: ResetRelativeToEnum
nodes.documentation: The specification of whether resets occur relative to the first or last day of a calculation period.

nodes.name: InterpolationPeriodEnum
nodes.documentation: Defines applicable periods for interpolation.

nodes.name: Beneficiary
nodes.documentation: A type defining the beneficiary of the funds.

nodes.name: CommodityRelativePaymentDates
nodes.documentation: The Payment Dates of the trade relative to the Calculation Periods.

nodes.name: DirectionalLeg
nodes.documentation: A type describing return which is driven by a Variance Calculation.

nodes.name: AccountName
nodes.documentation: The data type used for the name of the account.

nodes.name: InterestCalculationMethodEnum
nodes.documentation: >Defines whether agent bank is making an interest payment based on the lender pro-rata share at the end of the period or based on the lender position throughout the period. Agent Banks decide which way to calculate the interest for a deal.

nodes.name: EquityValuation
nodes.documentation: A type for defining how and when an equity option is to be valued.

nodes.name: upperBarrier
nodes.documentation: A type defining a number specified as non negative decimal greater than 0 inclusive.

nodes.name: Party
nodes.documentation: A type defining a legal entity or a subdivision of a legal entity.Parties can perform multiple roles in a trade lifecycle. For example, the principal parties obligated to make payments from time to time during the term of the trade, but may include other parties involved in, or incidental to, the trade, such as parties acting in the role of novation transferor/transferee, broker, calculation agent, etc. In FpML roles are defined in multiple places within a document.

nodes.name: AmountReference
nodes.documentation: Specifies a reference to a monetary amount.

nodes.name: type
nodes.documentation: The type of telephone number used to reach a contact.

nodes.name: Money
nodes.documentation: A type defining a currency amount.

nodes.name: ReportSectionIdentification
nodes.documentation: A type that allows the specific report and section to be identified.

nodes.name: ReportingRegimeName
nodes.documentation: An identifier of an reporting regime or format used for regulatory reporting, for example DoddFrankAct, MiFID, HongKongOTCDRepository, etc.

nodes.name: strikeQuoteBasis
nodes.documentation: A type which permits the Dual Currency strike quote basis to be expressed in terms of the deposit and alternate currencies.

nodes.name: dayOfWeek
nodes.documentation: A day of the seven-day week.

nodes.name: EuropeanExercise
nodes.documentation: A type defining the exercise period for a European style option together with any rules governing the notional amount of the underlying which can be exercised on any given exercise date and any associated exercise fees.

nodes.name: NotionalReference
nodes.documentation: A reference to the notional amount.

nodes.name: DividendConditions
nodes.documentation: A type describing the conditions governing the payment of dividends to the receiver of the equity return. With the exception of the dividend payout ratio, which is defined for each of the underlying components.

nodes.name: BusinessUnit
nodes.documentation: A type that represents information about a unit within an organization.

nodes.name: AveragePriceLeg
nodes.documentation: The average price leg of an average price commodity bullion or non-precious metal forward transaction.

nodes.name: numberOfOptions
nodes.documentation: A type defining a number specified as non negative decimal greater than 0 inclusive.

nodes.name: PartyPortfolioName
nodes.documentation: A type to represent a portfolio name for a particular party.

nodes.name: BrokerConfirmation
nodes.documentation: Identifies the market sector in which the trade has been arranged.

nodes.name: EquityDerivativeShortFormBase
nodes.documentation: A type for defining the broker equity options.

nodes.name: Document
nodes.documentation: A type defining a content model that includes valuation (pricing and risk) data without expressing any processing intention.

nodes.name: WeatherStationAirport
nodes.documentation: A code identifying a Weather Station Airport (based on the the IATA standard).

nodes.name: InterestLegCalculationPeriodDatesReference
nodes.documentation: Reference to the calculation period dates of the interest leg.

nodes.name: OptionExercise
nodes.documentation: A structure describing an option exercise.

nodes.name: Lag
nodes.documentation: An observation period that is offset from a Calculation Period.

nodes.name: PrincipalExchanges
nodes.documentation: A type defining which principal exchanges occur for the stream.

nodes.name: PartyName
nodes.documentation: The data type used for the legal name of an organization.

nodes.name: PositionId
nodes.documentation: A unique identifier for the position. The id attribute is defined for intradocument referencing.

nodes.name: DividendPaymentDate
nodes.documentation: A type describing the date on which the dividend will be paid/received. This type is also used to specify the date on which the FX rate will be determined, when applicable.

nodes.name: SettlementTypeEnum
nodes.documentation: Shows how the transaction is to be settled when it is exercised.

nodes.name: NotionalStepRule
nodes.documentation: A type defining a parametric representation of the notional step schedule, i.e. parameters used to generate the notional balance on each step date. The step change in notional can be expressed in terms of either a fixed amount or as a percentage of either the initial notional or previous notional amount. This parametric representation is intended to cover the more common amortizing/accreting.

nodes.name: TradeMaturity
nodes.documentation: A structure describing a trade maturing.

nodes.name: ExerciseFeeSchedule
nodes.documentation: A type to define a fee or schedule of fees to be payable on the exercise of an option. This fee may be defined as an amount or a percentage of the notional exercised.

nodes.name: ConfirmationDisputed
nodes.documentation: A message indicating that a confirmation has not been agreed by a counterparty.

nodes.name: TerminatingEvent
nodes.documentation: A type that describes why a trade terminated.

nodes.name: DataDocument
nodes.documentation: A type defining a content model that includes valuation (pricing and risk) data without expressing any processing intention.

nodes.name: PricingDataPointCoordinate
nodes.documentation: A set of index values that identify a pricing data point. For example: (strike = 17%, expiration = 6M, term = 1Y.

nodes.name: MasterConfirmation
nodes.documentation: An entity for defining the master confirmation agreement executed between the parties.

nodes.name: Knock
nodes.documentation: Knock In means option to exercise comes into existence. Knock Out means option to exercise goes out of existence.

nodes.name: GasPhysicalLeg
nodes.documentation: Physically settled leg of a physically settled gas transaction.

nodes.name: FloatingRateCalculation
nodes.documentation: A type defining the floating rate and definitions relating to the calculation of floating rate amounts.

nodes.name: ElectricityDeliveryUnitFirm
nodes.documentation: The physical delivery obligation options specific to a unit firm transaction.

nodes.name: AdjustableDateOrRelativeDateSequence
nodes.documentation: A type describing a date defined as subject to adjustment or defined in reference to another date through one or several date offsets.

nodes.name: CorrespondentInformation
nodes.documentation: A type that describes the information to identify a correspondent bank that will make delivery of the funds on the paying bank's behalf in the country where the payment is to be made.

nodes.name: EnvironmentalProductTypeEnum
nodes.documentation: Emissions Product (e.g. allowance or CER).

nodes.name: InstrumentSet
nodes.documentation: A collection of instruments usable for quotation purposes. In future releases, quotable derivative assets may be added after the underlying asset.

nodes.name: Payment
nodes.documentation: A type for defining payments. In Transparency view, normally the payer and receiver party references are not used; however they may be provided if necessary for administrative activities such as Reporting Party Determination in FX.

nodes.name: StrikeSpread
nodes.documentation: A type for defining a strike spread feature.

nodes.name: EquityPremium
nodes.documentation: A type used to describe the amount paid for an equity option.

nodes.name: VersionedContractId
nodes.documentation: Contract Id with Version Support

nodes.name: VerificationStatus
nodes.documentation: The verification status of the position as reported by the sender (Verified, Disputed).

nodes.name: Swaption
nodes.documentation: A type to define an option on a swap.

nodes.name: CommoditySwapLeg
nodes.documentation: The average price leg of an average price commodity bullion or non-precious metal forward transaction.

nodes.name: SettlementPriceSource
nodes.documentation: The source from which the settlement price is to be obtained, e.g. a Reuters page, Prezzo di Riferimento, etc.

nodes.name: FxAverageRateObservationSchedule
nodes.documentation: A type that describes average rate options rate observations. This is used to describe a parametric frequency of rate observations against a particular rate. Typical frequencies might include daily, every Friday, etc.

nodes.name: LengthUnitEnum
nodes.documentation: Used for indicating the length unit in the Resource type.

nodes.name: numberOfIndexUnits
nodes.documentation: A type defining a number specified as non negative decimal greater than 0 inclusive.

nodes.name: Trigger
nodes.documentation: Trigger point at which feature is effective.

nodes.name: AccountReference
nodes.documentation: Reference to an account.

nodes.name: SpreadSchedule
nodes.documentation: Adds an optional spread type element to the Schedule to identify a long or short spread value.

nodes.name: CommodityProductGrade
nodes.documentation: A scheme identifying the grade of physical commodity product to be delivered.

nodes.name: Rate
nodes.documentation: A type defining a floating rate.

nodes.name: triggerRate
nodes.documentation: A type defining a number specified as positive decimal greater than 0 exclusive.

nodes.name: AssetPool
nodes.documentation: Characterise the asset pool behind an asset backed bond.

nodes.name: OptionExpiryBase
nodes.documentation: A structure describing an option expiring.

nodes.name: YieldCurve
nodes.documentation: A generic yield curve object, which can be valued in a variety of ways.

nodes.name: flatRate
nodes.documentation: The method by which the Flat Rate is calculated for a commodity freight transaction.

nodes.name: TelephoneTypeEnum
nodes.documentation: The type of telephone number used to reach a contact.

nodes.name: ExtendibleProvisionAdjustedDates
nodes.documentation: A type defining the adjusted dates associated with a provision to extend a swap.

nodes.name: PricingStructureReference
nodes.documentation: Reference to a pricing structure or any derived components (i.e. yield curve).

nodes.name: BusinessProcess
nodes.documentation: A type that can be used to identify the type of business process in a request. Examples include Allocation, Clearing, Confirmation, etc.

nodes.name: ValuationDatesReference
nodes.documentation: Reference to a Valuation dates node.

nodes.name: InterestShortfallCapEnum
nodes.documentation: The specification of the interest shortfall cap, applicable to mortgage derivatives.

nodes.name: SettlementRateSource
nodes.documentation: A type describing the method for obtaining a settlement rate.

nodes.name: AveragingMethodEnum
nodes.documentation: The method of calculation to be used when averaging rates. Per ISDA 2000 Definitions, Section 6.2. Certain Definitions Relating to Floating Amounts.

nodes.name: CommodityDeliveryRisk
nodes.documentation: A scheme identifying how the parties to the trade aportion responsibility for the delivery of the commodity product (for example Free On Board, Cost, Insurance, Freight)

nodes.name: SplitSettlement
nodes.documentation: A type that supports the division of a gross settlement amount into a number of split settlements, each requiring its own settlement instruction.

nodes.name: ElectricityTransmissionContingency
nodes.documentation: A structure to specify the tranmission contingency and the party that bears the obligation.

nodes.name: ExerciseNotice
nodes.documentation: A type defining to whom and where notice of execution should be given. The partyReference refers to one of the principal parties of the trade. If present the exerciseNoticePartyReference refers to a party, other than the principal party, to whome notice should be given.

nodes.name: ConfirmationRetracted
nodes.documentation: A message indicating that a confirmation request has been withdrawn by the submitter.

nodes.name: BusinessDayAdjustments
nodes.documentation: A type defining the business day convention and financial business centers used for adjusting any relevant date if it would otherwise fall on a day that is not a business day in the specified business centers.

nodes.name: CorrelationAmount
nodes.documentation: Correlation Amount.

nodes.name: PersonId
nodes.documentation: An identifier used to identify an individual person.

nodes.name: quoteBasis
nodes.documentation: How an exchange rate is quoted.

nodes.name: FxCashSettlement
nodes.documentation: A type that is used for describing cash settlement of an option / non deliverable forward. It includes the currency to settle into together with the fixings required to calculate the currency amount.

nodes.name: BusinessEventIdentifier
nodes.documentation: A type defining an event identifier issued by the indicated party.

nodes.name: QuoteBasisEnum
nodes.documentation: How an exchange rate is quoted.

nodes.name: PortfolioReference
nodes.documentation: A structure used to group together individual messages that can be acted on at a group level.

nodes.name: WeeklyRollConventionEnum
nodes.documentation: The specification of a weekly roll day.

nodes.name: AssetValuation
nodes.documentation: A structure that holds a set of measures about an asset, including possibly their sensitivities.

nodes.name: LegIdentifier
nodes.documentation: Version aware identification of a leg.

nodes.name: CompoundingRate
nodes.documentation: A type defining a compounding rate. The compounding interest can either point back to the floating rate calculation of interest calculation node on the Interest Leg, or be defined specifically.

nodes.name: ValuationPostponement
nodes.documentation: Specifies how long to wait to get a quote from a settlement rate option upon a price source disruption.

nodes.name: BulletPayment
nodes.documentation: A product to represent a single cashflow.

nodes.name: minimumExclusive
nodes.documentation: A type defining a number specified as positive decimal greater than 0 exclusive.

nodes.name: AbsoluteTolerance
nodes.documentation: The acceptable tolerance in the delivered quantity of a physical commodity product in terms of a number of units of that product.

nodes.name: CoalProduct
nodes.documentation: A type defining the characteristics of the coal being traded in a physically settled gas transaction.

nodes.name: ValuationScenario
nodes.documentation: A set of rules for generating a valuation.

nodes.name: BusinessCenters
nodes.documentation: A type for defining business day calendar used in determining whether a day is a business day or not. A list of business day calendar locations may be ordered in the document alphabetically based on business day calendar location code. An FpML document containing an unordered business day calendar location list is still regarded as a conformant document.

nodes.name: ExternalDocument
nodes.documentation: A for holding information about documents external to the FpML.

nodes.name: maximumNumberOfOptions
nodes.documentation: A type defining a number specified as non negative decimal greater than 0 inclusive.

nodes.name: PartyMessageInformation
nodes.documentation: A type defining additional information that may be recorded against a message.

nodes.name: TradeId
nodes.documentation: A trade reference identifier allocated by a party. FpML does not define the domain values associated with this element. Note that the domain values for this element are not strictly an enumerated list.

nodes.name: InstrumentTradeDetails
nodes.documentation: The economics of a trade of a multiply traded instrument.

nodes.name: MainPublication
nodes.documentation: A type to define the main publication source.

nodes.name: PaymentDatesReference
nodes.documentation: Reference to a payment dates structure.

nodes.name: quotationMethod
nodes.documentation: The specification of the type of quotation rate to be obtained from each cash settlement reference bank.

nodes.name: InterestLeg
nodes.documentation: A type describing the fixed income leg of the equity swap.

nodes.name: CommodityDayTypeEnum
nodes.documentation: A day type classification used in counting the number of days between two dates for a commodity transaction.

nodes.name: PayRelativeToEnum
nodes.documentation: The specification of whether payments occur relative to the calculation period start or end date, or the reset date.

nodes.name: averagingInOut
nodes.documentation: The type of averaging used in an Asian option.

nodes.name: InterestAccrualsMethod
nodes.documentation: A type defining the way in which interests are accrued: the applicable rate (fixed or floating reference) and the compounding method.

nodes.name: CommodityPhysicalQuantity
nodes.documentation: A type defining the physical quantity of the commodity to be delivered.

nodes.name: CommodityHubCode
nodes.documentation: A scheme identifying the code for a hub or other reference for a physically settled commodity trade.

nodes.name: BusinessCenter
nodes.documentation: A code identifying a business day calendar location. A business day calendar location is drawn from the list identified by the business day calendar location scheme.

nodes.name: CompressionActivity
nodes.documentation: A type that shows how multiple trades have been combined into a result.

nodes.name: FxSingleLeg
nodes.documentation: A type defining either a spot or forward FX transactions.

nodes.name: SinglePartyOption
nodes.documentation: A type describing the buyer and seller of an option.

nodes.name: calculationAgentParty
nodes.documentation: The specification of how a calculation agent will be determined.

nodes.name: Calculation
nodes.documentation: A type definining the parameters used in the calculation of fixed or floating calculation period amounts.

nodes.name: ContractualDefinitions
nodes.documentation: The definitions, such as those published by ISDA, that will define the terms of the trade.

nodes.name: EquityEuropeanExercise
nodes.documentation: A type for defining exercise procedures associated with a European style exercise of an equity option.

nodes.name: OptionalEarlyTerminationAdjustedDates
nodes.documentation: A type defining the adjusted dates associated with an optional early termination provision.

nodes.name: QuoteTiming
nodes.documentation: The type of the time of the quote.

nodes.name: Tranche
nodes.documentation: This type represents a CDS Tranche.

nodes.name: EnvironmentalAbandonmentOfSchemeEnum
nodes.documentation: Upon the occurrence of an Abandonment of Scheme, as defined in clause (h)(iv) of the Emissions Annex, one of the following elections, the specific terms of which are set forth in clause (b)(iii) of the Emissions Annex, will govern the parties rights and obligations with respect to this Emissions Transaction. If none of the above options is selected, Option A(1) will apply.

nodes.name: YieldCurveMethod
nodes.documentation: A type defining the parameters required for each of the ISDA defined yield curve methods for cash settlement.

nodes.name: HourMinuteTime
nodes.documentation: A type defining a time specified in hh:mm:ss format where the second component must be '00', e.g. 11am would be represented as 11:00:00.

nodes.name: EquityStrike
nodes.documentation: A type for defining the strike price for an equity option. The strike price is either: (i) in respect of an index option transaction, the level of the relevant index specified or otherwise determined in the transaction; or (ii) in respect of a share option transaction, the price per share specified or otherwise determined in the transaction. This can be expressed either as a percentage of notional amount or as an absolute value.

nodes.name: rateTreatment
nodes.documentation: The specification of methods for converting rates from one basis to another.

nodes.name: TradeHeader
nodes.documentation: A type defining trade related information which is not product specific.

nodes.name: PositionOriginEnum
nodes.documentation: A type used to report how a position originated.

nodes.name: DerivedValuationScenario
nodes.documentation: A valuation scenario that is derived from another valuation scenario.

nodes.name: RequestEventStatus
nodes.documentation: A type defining the content model for a message allowing one party to query the status of one event (trade or post-trade event) previously sent to another party.

nodes.name: TradeIdentifier
nodes.documentation: A type defining one or more trade identifiers allocated to the trade by a party. A link identifier allows the trade to be associated with other related trades, e.g. trades forming part of a larger structured transaction. It is expected that for external communication of trade there will be only one tradeId sent in the document per party.

nodes.name: PricingDataPointCoordinateReference
nodes.documentation: Reference to a Pricing Data Point Coordinate.

nodes.name: minimumInclusive
nodes.documentation: A type defining a number specified as positive decimal greater than 0 exclusive.

nodes.name: FxDigitalOption
nodes.documentation: Describes an option having a triggerable fixed payout.

nodes.name: QuantityReference
nodes.documentation: A pointer tyle reference to a Quantity defined elsewhere.

nodes.name: ElectricityPhysicalDeliveryQuantity
nodes.documentation: A type defining the physical quantity of the electricity to be delivered.

nodes.name: EventId
nodes.documentation: A post-trade event reference identifier allocated by a party. FpML does not define the domain values associated with this element. Note that the domain values for this element are not strictly an enumerated list.

nodes.name: NegativeInterestRateTreatmentEnum
nodes.documentation: The method of calculating payment obligations when a floating rate is negative (either due to a quoted negative floating rate or by operation of a spread that is subtracted from the floating rate).

nodes.name: RequestAllocation
nodes.documentation: A message requesting that a trade be split among several accounts.

nodes.name: weight
nodes.documentation: A type defining a number specified as non negative decimal greater than 0 inclusive.

nodes.name: GasDelivery
nodes.documentation: The specification of the gas to be delivered.

nodes.name: Withdrawal
nodes.documentation: A structure describing the removal of a trade from a service, such as a reporting service.

nodes.name: DividendPeriodEnum
nodes.documentation: Defines the First Period or the Second Period, as specified in the 2002 ISDA Equity Derivatives Definitions.

nodes.name: CompressionType
nodes.documentation: A type that identifies the type of trade amalgamation, for example netting or portfolio compression.

nodes.name: ClearanceSystem
nodes.documentation: Unless otherwise specified, the principal clearance system customarily used for settling trades in the relevant underlying.

nodes.name: AbstractEvent
nodes.documentation: Abstract base type for all events.

nodes.name: TimeTypeEnum
nodes.documentation: Defines points in the day when equity option exercise and valuation can occur.

nodes.name: CalculationPeriodDatesReference
nodes.documentation: Reference to a calculation period dates component.

nodes.name: CommoditySwaption
nodes.documentation: Commodity Swaption.

nodes.name: RelativeDates
nodes.documentation: A type describing a set of dates defined as relative to another set of dates.

nodes.name: CashPhysicalEnum
nodes.documentation: Shows how the transaction is to be settled when it is exercised.

nodes.name: SimplePayment
nodes.documentation: A complex type to specified payments in a simpler fashion than the Payment type. This construct should be used from the version 4.3 onwards.

nodes.name: ExerciseProcedure
nodes.documentation: A type describing how notice of exercise should be given. This can be either manual or automatic.

nodes.name: InterestLegCalculationPeriodDates
nodes.documentation: Component that holds the various dates used to specify the interest leg of the return swap. It is used to define the InterestPeriodDates identifyer.

nodes.name: FlatRateEnum
nodes.documentation: The method by which the Flat Rate is calculated for a commodity freight transaction.

nodes.name: GasProductTypeEnum
nodes.documentation: The type of gas product.

nodes.name: RegulatorId
nodes.documentation: An ID assigned by a regulator to an organization registered with it. (NOTE: should this just by represented by an alternate party ID?)

nodes.name: delisting
nodes.documentation: Defines the consequences of nationalisation, insolvency and delisting events relating to the underlying.

nodes.name: BasicAssetValuation
nodes.documentation: A structure that holds a set of measures about an asset.

nodes.name: CoalProductSource
nodes.documentation: A scheme identifying the sources of coal for a physically settled coal trade.

nodes.name: FxTouch
nodes.documentation: Describes an FX touch condition.

nodes.name: voltage
nodes.documentation: A type defining a number specified as positive decimal greater than 0 exclusive.

nodes.name: productType
nodes.documentation: Emissions Product (e.g. allowance or CER).

nodes.name: AveragingInOutEnum
nodes.documentation: The type of averaging used in an Asian option.

nodes.name: DayTypeEnum
nodes.documentation: A day type classification used in counting the number of days between two dates.

nodes.name: CreditSupportAgreement
nodes.documentation: The agreement executed between the parties and intended to govern collateral arrangement for all OTC derivatives transactions between those parties.

nodes.name: DeliveryDatesEnum
nodes.documentation: In respect of a Transaction and a Commodity Reference Price, the relevant date or month for delivery of the underlying Commodity.

nodes.name: Discounting
nodes.documentation: A type defining discounting information. The 2000 ISDA definitions, section 8.4. discounting (related to the calculation of a discounted fixed amount or floating amount) apply. This type must only be included if discounting applies.

nodes.name: PointValue
nodes.documentation: Constrains the forward point tick/pip factor to 1, 0.1, 0.01, 0.001, etc.

nodes.name: CommodityPayRelativeToEvent
nodes.documentation: A scheme identifying the physical event relative to which payment occurs.

nodes.name: IssuerId
nodes.documentation: The data type used for issuer identifiers.

nodes.name: PriceQuoteUnits
nodes.documentation: The units in which a price is quoted.

nodes.name: FixedRate
nodes.documentation: The calculation period fixed rate. A per annum rate, expressed as a decimal. A fixed rate of 5% would be represented as 0.05.

nodes.name: StrikeQuoteBasisEnum
nodes.documentation: The specification of how an FX OTC option strike price is quoted.

nodes.name: discountingType
nodes.documentation: The method of calculating discounted payment amounts

nodes.name: BullionPhysicalLeg
nodes.documentation: Physically settled leg of a physically settled Bullion Transaction.

nodes.name: FutureId
nodes.documentation: A type defining a short form unique identifier for a future contract.

nodes.name: StepRelativeToEnum
nodes.documentation: The specification of whether a percentage rate change, used to calculate a change in notional outstanding, is expressed as a percentage of the initial notional amount or the previously outstanding notional amount.

nodes.name: CommoditySpreadSchedule
nodes.documentation: The Spread per Calculation Period. There must be a Spread specified for each Calculation Period, regardless of whether the Spread changes or remains the same between periods.

nodes.name: TradeWrapper
nodes.documentation: A structure that contains a business event.

nodes.name: SettlementInformation
nodes.documentation: A type that represents the choice of methods for settling a potential currency payment resulting from a trade: by means of a standard settlement instruction, by netting it out with other payments, or with an explicit settlement instruction.

nodes.name: ReferenceLevelUnit
nodes.documentation: CPD Reference Level: millimeters or inches of daily precipitation HDD Reference Level: degree-days CDD Reference Level: degree-days.

nodes.name: dividendDateReference
nodes.documentation: The reference to a dividend date.

nodes.name: RateReference
nodes.documentation: Reference to any rate (floating, inflation) derived from the abstract Rate component.

nodes.name: LinkId
nodes.documentation: The data type used for link identifiers.

nodes.name: FxTenorPeriodEnum
nodes.documentation: The specification of a time period containing values such as Today, Tomorrow etc.

nodes.name: BrokerEquityOption
nodes.documentation: A type for defining the broker equity options.

nodes.name: DividendAdjustment
nodes.documentation: Container for Dividend Adjustment Periods, which are used to calculate the Deviation between Expected Dividend and Actual Dividend in that Period.

nodes.name: ReportingRole
nodes.documentation: A type containing a code representing the role of a party in a report, e.g. the originator, the recipient, the counterparty, etc. This is used to clarify which participant's information is being reported.

nodes.name: Compounding
nodes.documentation: Specifies the compounding method and the compounding rate.

nodes.name: FrequencyType
nodes.documentation: Frequency Type.

nodes.name: BusinessDayAdjustmentsReference
nodes.documentation: Reference to a business day adjustments structure.

nodes.name: StartingDate
nodes.documentation: A type specifying the date from which the early termination clause can be exercised.

nodes.name: CoalAttributePercentage
nodes.documentation: The different options for specifying the attributes of a coal quality measure as a percentage of the measured value.

nodes.name: StrategyComponentIdentification
nodes.documentation: Associates trade identifiers with components of a strategy.

nodes.name: CommodityEuropeanExercise
nodes.documentation: A type for defining exercise procedures associated with a European style exercise of a commodity option.

nodes.name: SettlementInstruction
nodes.documentation: A type that models a complete instruction for settling a currency payment, including the settlement method to be used, the correspondent bank, any intermediary banks and the ultimate beneficary.

nodes.name: MoneyBase
nodes.documentation: A type defining a currency amount as at a future value date.

nodes.name: ResponseMessage
nodes.documentation: A type refining the generic message content model to make it specific to response messages.

nodes.name: CommodityPhysicalAmericanExercise
nodes.documentation: The parameters for defining the expiration date(s) and time(s) for an American style option.

nodes.name: ResourceLength
nodes.documentation: The type that indicates the length of the resource.

nodes.name: ExecutionRetracted
nodes.documentation: A message retracting a notification to a party that a trade execution has occurred. (Typically this is sent by an execution platform to a participant.)

nodes.name: ElectricityPhysicalQuantity
nodes.documentation: The quantity of gas to be delivered.

nodes.name: ElectricityPhysicalDeliveryQuantitySchedule
nodes.documentation: Allows the documentation of a shaped quantity trade where the quantity changes over the life of the transaction.

nodes.name: FxSpotRateSource
nodes.documentation: A type defining the source and time for an fx rate.

nodes.name: VarianceLeg
nodes.documentation: A type describing return which is driven by a Variance Calculation.

nodes.name: FxOptionPayout
nodes.documentation: A type that contains full details of a predefined fixed payout which may occur (or not) in a Barrier Option or Digital Option when a trigger event occurs (or not).

nodes.name: SpreadScheduleReference
nodes.documentation: Provides a reference to a spread schedule.

nodes.name: TradeChangeBase
nodes.documentation: A structure describing a trade change.

nodes.name: PortfolioName
nodes.documentation: The data type used for portfolio names.

nodes.name: DividendSwapTransactionSupplement
nodes.documentation: A Dividend Swap Transaction Supplement.

nodes.name: ScheduleReference
nodes.documentation: Reference to a schedule of rates or amounts.

nodes.name: EnvironmentalPhysicalLeg
nodes.documentation: Physically settled leg of a physically settled emissions allowance transaction.

nodes.name: BusinessDateRange
nodes.documentation: A type defining a range of contiguous business days by defining an unadjusted first date, an unadjusted last date and a business day convention and business centers for adjusting the first and last dates if they would otherwise fall on a non business day in the specified business centers. The days between the first and last date must also be good business days in the specified centers to be counted in the range.

nodes.name: MarkToMarketConventionEnum
nodes.documentation: The type of mark to market convention.

nodes.name: TermCurve
nodes.documentation: A curve consisting only of values over a term. This is a restricted form of One Dimensional Structure.

nodes.name: ConsentRefused
nodes.documentation: A message indicating that the sender does not grant consent for the recipient to perform the requested action.

nodes.name: PersonReference
nodes.documentation: Reference to an individual.

nodes.name: CashflowNotional
nodes.documentation: The notional/principal value/quantity/volume used to compute the cashflow.

nodes.name: CommodityRelativeExpirationDates
nodes.documentation: The Expiration Dates of the trade relative to the Calculation Periods.

nodes.name: DualCurrencyStrikeQuoteBasisEnum
nodes.documentation: A type which permits the Dual Currency strike quote basis to be expressed in terms of the deposit and alternate currencies.

nodes.name: triggerType
nodes.documentation: The specification of whether an option would trigger or expire depending upon whether the spot rate is above or below the barrier rate.

nodes.name: Loan
nodes.documentation: A type describing a loan underlying asset.

nodes.name: soldAs
nodes.documentation: Specifies whether the option is a call or a put.

nodes.name: PassThrough
nodes.documentation: Type which contains pass through payments.

nodes.name: Strike
nodes.documentation: A type describing a single cap or floor rate.

nodes.name: amount
nodes.documentation: A type defining a number specified as non negative decimal greater than 0 inclusive.

nodes.name: AverageDailyTradingVolumeLimit
nodes.documentation: To indicate the limitation percentage and limitation period.

nodes.name: FloatingRateIndex
nodes.documentation: The ISDA Floating Rate Option, i.e. the floating rate index.

nodes.name: DividendCompositionEnum
nodes.documentation: Defines how the composition of dividends is to be determined.

nodes.name: FixedPriceLeg
nodes.documentation: Fixed Price Leg of a Commodity Swap.

nodes.name: InstrumentTradePricing
nodes.documentation: A structure describing the price paid for the instrument.

nodes.name: NotionalAmountReference
nodes.documentation: A reference to the notional amount.

nodes.name: Exception
nodes.documentation: A type defining the basic content for a message sent to inform another system that some exception has been detected.

nodes.name: AssetOrTermPointOrPricingStructureReference
nodes.documentation: Reference to an underlying asset, term point or pricing structure (yield curve).

nodes.name: ServiceAdvisory
nodes.documentation: A type defining the content model for a human-readable notification to the users of a service.

nodes.name: FxEuropeanExercise
nodes.documentation: Describes the characteristics for European exercise of FX products.

nodes.name: ReturnLegValuation
nodes.documentation: A type describing the initial and final valuation of the underlyer.

nodes.name: PassThroughItem
nodes.documentation: Type to represent a single pass through payment.

nodes.name: GrossCashflow
nodes.documentation: A payment component owed from one party to the other for the cash flow date. This payment component should by of only a single type, e.g. a fee or a cashflow from a cashflow stream.

nodes.name: ServiceAdvisoryCategory
nodes.documentation: A type that can be used to describe the category of an advisory message, e.g.. Availability, Rules, Products, etc., etc..

nodes.name: ServiceProcessingEvent
nodes.documentation: A type that can be used to describe a stage or step in processing provided by a service, for example processing completed.

nodes.name: PercentageRule
nodes.documentation: A type defining a content model for a calculation rule defined as percentage of the notional amount.

nodes.name: TimezoneLocation
nodes.documentation: A geophraphic location for the purposes of defining a prevailing time according to the tz database.

nodes.name: CrossRate
nodes.documentation: A type that is used for including the currency exchange rates used to cross between the traded currencies for non-base currency FX contracts.

nodes.name: correlationStrikePrice
nodes.documentation: A type defining a number specified as a decimal between -1 and 1 inclusive.

nodes.name: CommodityPhysicalQuantitySchedule
nodes.documentation: The Quantity per Delivery Period. There must be a Quantity step specified for each Delivery Period, regardless of whether the Quantity changes or remains the same between periods.

nodes.name: CancellationEvent
nodes.documentation: The adjusted dates for a specific cancellation date, including the adjusted exercise date and adjusted termination date.

nodes.name: GasQuality
nodes.documentation: The quantity of gas to be delivered.

nodes.name: CommissionDenominationEnum
nodes.documentation: The unit in which a commission is denominated.

nodes.name: commissionDenomination
nodes.documentation: The unit in which a commission is denominated.

nodes.name: SensitivityDefinition
nodes.documentation: A set of characteristics describing a sensitivity.

nodes.name: initialStockLoanRate
nodes.documentation: A type defining a percentage specified as decimal from 0 to 1. A percentage of 5% would be represented as 0.05.

nodes.name: ReturnSwapAdditionalPayment
nodes.documentation: A type describing the additional payment(s) between the principal parties to the trade. This component extends some of the features of the additionalPayment component previously developed in FpML. Appropriate discussions will determine whether it would be appropriate to extend the shared component in order to meet the further requirements of equity swaps.

nodes.name: DividendEntitlementEnum
nodes.documentation: The date on which the receiver of the equity return is entitled to the dividend.

nodes.name: ExchangeTraded
nodes.documentation: An exchange traded equity asset.

nodes.name: Index
nodes.documentation: A published index whose price depends on exchange traded constituents.

nodes.name: Representations
nodes.documentation: A type for defining ISDA 2002 Equity Derivative Representations.

nodes.name: PayoutEnum
nodes.documentation: The specification of how an FX OTC option with a trigger payout will be paid if the trigger condition is met. The contract will specify whether the payout will occur immediately or on the original value date of the option.

nodes.name: CouponType
nodes.documentation: Defines a scheme of values for specifiying if the bond has a variable coupon, step-up/down coupon or a zero-coupon.

nodes.name: QueryPortfolio
nodes.documentation: A type representing a portfolio obtained by querying the set of trades held in a repository. It contains trades matching the intersection of all criteria specified using one or more queryParameters or trades matching the union of two or more child queryPortfolios.

nodes.name: PriceExpressionEnum
nodes.documentation: The mode of expression of a price.

nodes.name: ElectricityProduct
nodes.documentation: The specification of the electricity to be delivered.

nodes.name: FxCurveValuation
nodes.documentation: A valuation of an FX curve object., which includes pricing inputs and term structures for fx forwards.

nodes.name: GenericAgreement
nodes.documentation: An entity for defining a generic agreement executed between two parties for any purpose.

nodes.name: WithdrawalReason
nodes.documentation: A type that describes why a trade was withdrawn.

nodes.name: PaymentBase
nodes.documentation: A structure representing a pending dividend or coupon payment.

nodes.name: DividendLeg
nodes.documentation: Floating Payment Leg of a Dividend Swap.

nodes.name: EquityDerivativeBase
nodes.documentation: A type for defining the broker equity options.

nodes.name: CoalDeliveryPoint
nodes.documentation: A scheme identifying the types of the Delivery Point for a physically settled coal trade.

nodes.name: ParametricAdjustmentPoint
nodes.documentation: A value of the adjustment point, consisting of the x value and the corresponding y value.

nodes.name: TradeChangeAdvice
nodes.documentation: Defines the structure for a message indicating that a trade is being changed due to a non-negotiated event.

nodes.name: RequestExecutionRetracted
nodes.documentation: A message withdrawing a request that an order be executed.

nodes.name: RequestRetransmission
nodes.documentation: A message to request that a message be retransmitted. The original message will typically be a component of a group of messages, such as a portfolio or a report in multiple parts.

nodes.name: NonNegativeAmountSchedule
nodes.documentation: A type defining a currency amount or a currency amount schedule.

nodes.name: NetAndGross
nodes.documentation: A structure including a net and/or a gross amount and possibly fees and commissions.

nodes.name: ValuationDocument
nodes.documentation: A type defining a content model that includes valuation (pricing and risk) data without expressing any processing intention.

nodes.name: ClearingStatus
nodes.documentation: A message providing the current status of a clearing request.

nodes.name: AutomaticExercise
nodes.documentation: A type to define automatic exercise of a swaption. With automatic exercise the option is deemed to have exercised if it is in the money by more than the threshold amount on the exercise date.

nodes.name: NotificationMessageHeader
nodes.documentation: A type that refines the generic message header to match the requirements of a NotificationMessage.

nodes.name: CashSettlement
nodes.documentation: A type to define the cash settlement terms for a product where cash settlement is applicable.

nodes.name: PaymentBaseExtended
nodes.documentation: A complex type to specify non negative payments.

nodes.name: dayType
nodes.documentation: A day type classification used in counting the number of days between two dates.

nodes.name: nonCashDividendTreatment
nodes.documentation: Defines treatment of non-cash dividends.

nodes.name: EnvironmentalProductApplicableLaw
nodes.documentation: TBD.

nodes.name: GasDeliveryPeriods
nodes.documentation: The different options for specifying the Delivery Periods for a physically settled gas trade.

nodes.name: CommodityInformationSource
nodes.documentation: A type defining the source of a commodity rate, price or index or of a market rate or of a conversion factor (e.g. a fx conversion factor).

nodes.name: side
nodes.documentation: The side from which perspective a value is quoted.

nodes.name: ScheduledDate
nodes.documentation: An servicing date relevant for a trade structure, such as a payment or a reset.

nodes.name: valuationTimeType
nodes.documentation: Defines points in the day when equity option exercise and valuation can occur.

nodes.name: FxOptionFeatures
nodes.documentation: A type describing the features that may be present in an FX option.

nodes.name: MethodOfAdjustmentEnum
nodes.documentation: Defines how adjustments will be made to the contract should one or more of the extraordinary events occur.

nodes.name: WeatherCalculationPeriod
nodes.documentation: The schedule of Calculation Period First Days and Lasts Days. If there is only one First Day - Last Day pair then the First is equal to the Effective Date and the Last Day is equal to the Termination Date.

nodes.name: CommodityNotionalQuantity
nodes.documentation: Commodity Notional.

nodes.name: CalculationPeriod
nodes.documentation: A type defining the parameters used in the calculation of a fixed or floating rate calculation period amount. This type forms part of cashflows representation of a swap stream.

nodes.name: applicableDay
nodes.documentation: A day of the seven-day week.

nodes.name: SettlementTermsReference
nodes.documentation: Reference to a settlement terms derived construct (cashSettlementTerms or physicalSettlementTerms).

nodes.name: DerivativeCalculationMethod
nodes.documentation: The method by which a derivative is computed.

nodes.name: NonNegativeMoney
nodes.documentation: A type defining a currency amount as at a future value date.

nodes.name: CommodityDeliveryPoint
nodes.documentation: A scheme identifying the types of the Delivery Point for a physically settled commodity trade.

nodes.name: CommodityPipeline
nodes.documentation: The pipeline through which the physical commodity will be delivered.

nodes.name: PositionStatusEnum
nodes.documentation: The type of averaging used in an Asian option.A type used to report the status of a position.

nodes.name: QuotationStyleEnum
nodes.documentation: Indicates the actual quotation style of of PointsUpFront or TradedSpread that was used to quote this trade.

nodes.name: TriggerTimeTypeEnum
nodes.documentation: The time of day which would be considered for valuing the knock event.

nodes.name: ExecutionNotification
nodes.documentation: A message notifying a party that a trade execution has occurred. (Typically this is sent by an execution platform to a participant.)

nodes.name: ClearingRefused
nodes.documentation: A message indicating that a clearing request has not been acted on due to a business decision and therefore no trade has been cleared.

nodes.name: marketDisruptionEvents
nodes.documentation: The specification of how market disruption events will be represented.

nodes.name: StrikeSchedule
nodes.documentation: A type describing a schedule of cap or floor rates.

nodes.name: ResourceId
nodes.documentation: The data type used for resource identifiers.

nodes.name: DividendPayout
