nodes.documentation: A type describing the dividend payout ratio associated with an equity underlyer. In certain cases the actual ratio is not known on trade inception, and only general conditions are then specified.

nodes.name: EquityAsset
nodes.documentation: An exchange traded equity asset.

nodes.name: CorrelationValue
nodes.documentation: A type defining a number specified as a decimal between -1 and 1 inclusive.

nodes.name: Premium
nodes.documentation: A type for defining a premium.

nodes.name: FloatingPriceLeg
nodes.documentation: Floating Price Leg of a Commodity Swap.

nodes.name: category
nodes.documentation: Used in both the obligations and deliverable obligations of the credit default swap to represent a class or type of securities which apply.

nodes.name: Portfolio
nodes.documentation: A type representing an arbitary grouping of trade references.

nodes.name: PrincipalExchange
nodes.documentation: A type defining a principal exchange amount and adjusted exchange date. The type forms part of the cashflow representation of a swap stream.

nodes.name: StepBase
nodes.documentation: A type defining a step date and non-negative step value pair. This step definitions are used to define varying rate or amount schedules, e.g. a notional amortization or a step-up coupon schedule.

nodes.name: PayerReceiverEnum
nodes.documentation: The specification of an interest rate stream payer or receiver party.

nodes.name: pointValue
nodes.documentation: Constrains the forward point tick/pip factor to 1, 0.1, 0.01, 0.001, etc.

nodes.name: CalculationPeriodsScheduleReference
nodes.documentation: A pointer style reference to a calculation periods schedule defined elsewhere - note that this schedule consists of a parameterised schedule in a calculationPeriodsSchedule container.

nodes.name: AdjustableDate2
nodes.documentation: A type that is different from AdjustableDate in two regards. First, date adjustments can be specified with either a dateAdjustments element or a reference to an existing dateAdjustments element. Second, it does not require the specification of date adjustments.

nodes.name: NonNegativeSchedule
nodes.documentation: A type defining a currency amount or a currency amount schedule.

nodes.name: FutureValueAmount
nodes.documentation: A type defining a currency amount as at a future value date.

nodes.name: EquityExerciseValuationSettlement
nodes.documentation: A type for defining exercise procedures for equity options.

nodes.name: TradeUnderlyer2
nodes.documentation: The underlying asset/index/reference price etc. whose rate/price may be observed to compute the value of the cashflow. It can be an index, fixed rate, listed security, quoted currency pair, or a reference entity (for credit derivatives). For use with Generic products in Transparency reporting. Generic products define a product that represents an OTC derivative transaction whose economics are not fully described using an FpML schema. In other views, generic products are present for convenience to support internal messaging and workflows that are cross-product. Generic products are not full trade representations as such they are not intended to be used for confirming trades.

nodes.name: PositivePayment
nodes.documentation: A complex type to specify positive payments.

nodes.name: PutCallEnum
nodes.documentation: Specifies whether the option is a call or a put.

nodes.name: IndustryClassification
nodes.documentation: A party's industry sector classification.

nodes.name: RequiredIdentifierDate
nodes.documentation: A date with a required identifier which can be referenced elsewhere.

nodes.name: PricingInputReplacement
nodes.documentation: The substitution of a pricing input (e.g. curve) for another, used in generating prices and risks for valuation scenarios.

nodes.name: barrierType
nodes.documentation: The specification of whether a barrier within an FX OTC option is a knockin or knockout, as well as whether it is a standard barrier or a reverse barrier.

nodes.name: payoutStyle
nodes.documentation: The specification of how an FX OTC option with a trigger payout will be paid if the trigger condition is met. The contract will specify whether the payout will occur immediately or on the original value date of the option.

nodes.name: DualCurrencyFeature
nodes.documentation: Describes the parameters for a dual currency deposit.

nodes.name: OptionType
nodes.documentation: A flexible description of the type or characteristics of an option or strategy, e.g. butterfly, condor, chooser. For use with Generic products in Transparency reporting. Generic products define a product that represents an OTC derivative transaction whose economics are not fully described using an FpML schema. In other views, generic products are present for convenience to support internal messaging and workflows that are cross-product. Generic products are not full trade representations as such they are not intended to be used for confirming trades.

nodes.name: PhysicalSwapLeg
nodes.documentation: Physically settled leg of a physically settled coal transaction.

nodes.name: QuotationRateTypeEnum
nodes.documentation: The specification of the type of quotation rate to be obtained from each cash settlement reference bank.

nodes.name: PaymentId
nodes.documentation: An identifier used to identify a matchable payment.

nodes.name: spotRate
nodes.documentation: A type defining a number specified as positive decimal greater than 0 exclusive.

nodes.name: CoalPhysicalLeg
nodes.documentation: Physically settled leg of a physically settled coal transaction.

nodes.name: Price
nodes.documentation: A type describing the strike price.

nodes.name: RequestConsent
nodes.documentation: A message requesting that the sender be authorized by the recipient to peform an action.

nodes.name: Swap
nodes.documentation: A type defining swap streams and additional payments between the principal parties involved in the swap.

nodes.name: FallbackReferencePrice
nodes.documentation: The method, prioritzed by the order it is listed in this element, to get a replacement rate for the disrupted settlement rate option.

nodes.name: ExecutionType
nodes.documentation: A type used to represent the type of market where a trade can be executed.

nodes.name: ThresholdTypeEnum
nodes.documentation: The type of threshold.

nodes.name: fixedStrike
nodes.documentation: A type defining a number specified as positive decimal greater than 0 exclusive.

nodes.name: VarianceSwapTransactionSupplement
nodes.documentation: A Variance Swap Transaction Supplement.

nodes.name: businessDayConvention
nodes.documentation: The convention for adjusting any relevant date if it would otherwise fall on a day that is not a valid business day. Note that FRN is included here as a type of business day convention although it does not strictly fall within ISDA's definition of a Business Day Convention and does not conform to the simple definition given above.

nodes.name: SensitivitySet
nodes.documentation: A collection of sensitivities. References a definition that explains the meaning/type of the sensitivities.

nodes.name: EventRequestAcknowledgement
nodes.documentation: Defines the structure for a message acknowledging an event request.

nodes.name: excessDividendAmount
nodes.documentation: Refers to one on the 3 Amounts

nodes.name: MarketDisruptionEventsEnum
nodes.documentation: The specification of how market disruption events will be represented.

nodes.name: SettlementPeriods
nodes.documentation: Specifies a set of Settlement Periods associated with an Electricity Transaction for delivery on an Applicable Day or for a series of Applicable Days.

nodes.name: WeatherStationWBAN
nodes.documentation: A code identifying a Weather Station WBAN.

nodes.name: PaymentReference
nodes.documentation: Reference to a payment.

nodes.name: postitive
nodes.documentation: A type defining a percentage specified as decimal from 0 to 1. A percentage of 5% would be represented as 0.05.

nodes.name: AccountId
nodes.documentation: The data type used for account identifiers.

nodes.name: Scheme
nodes.documentation: The base class for all types which define coding schemes.

nodes.name: shareForCombined
nodes.documentation: Defines the consequences of extraordinary events relating to the underlying.

nodes.name: ProductComponentIdentifier
nodes.documentation: A type defining a USI for the a subproduct component of a strategy.

nodes.name: FxFeature
nodes.documentation: A type for defining Fx Features.

nodes.name: triggerTimeType
nodes.documentation: The time of day which would be considered for valuing the knock event.

nodes.name: EquityDerivativeLongFormBase
nodes.documentation: type for defining the common features of equity derivatives.

nodes.name: DayCountFraction
nodes.documentation: The specification for how the number of days between two dates is calculated for purposes of calculation of a fixed or floating payment amount and the basis for how many days are assumed to be in a year. Day Count Fraction is an ISDA term. The equivalent AFB (Association Francaise de Banques) term is Calculation Basis.

nodes.name: AveragingSchedule
nodes.documentation: Method of generating a series of dates.

nodes.name: ReportingRegime
nodes.documentation: Provides information about how the information in this message is applicable to a regulatory reporting process.

nodes.name: PortfolioReferenceBase
nodes.documentation: A structure used to group together individual messages that can be acted on at a group level.

nodes.name: LegId
nodes.documentation: Leg identity.

nodes.name: SettlementPeriodsSchedule
nodes.documentation: The specification of the Settlement Periods in which the electricity will be delivered for a "shaped" trade i.e. where different Settlement Period ranges will apply to different periods of the trade.

nodes.name: recoveryFactor
nodes.documentation: A type defining a percentage specified as decimal from 0 to 1. A percentage of 5% would be represented as 0.05.

nodes.name: DifferenceSeverityEnum
nodes.documentation: The ISDA defined value indicating the severity of a difference.

nodes.name: CalculatedAmount
nodes.documentation: Calculation of a Variance Amount.

nodes.name: CreditEventNotificationRetracted
nodes.documentation: A message type retracting a previous credit event notification.

nodes.name: EndUserExceptionDeclaration
nodes.documentation: Records supporting information justifying an end user exception under 17 CFR part 39.

nodes.name: AssetReference
nodes.documentation: Reference to an underlying asset.

nodes.name: RoutingExplicitDetails
nodes.documentation: A type that models name, address and supplementary textual information for the purposes of identifying a party involved in the routing of a payment.

nodes.name: RequestTradeReferenceInformationUpdateRetracted
nodes.documentation: Defines the structure for a message retracting a request to updated information about trade.

nodes.name: InterestAccrualsCompoundingMethod
nodes.documentation: A type defining the way in which interests are accrued: the applicable rate (fixed or floating reference) and the compounding method.

nodes.name: CreditOptionStrike
nodes.documentation: A complex type to specify the strike of a credit swaption or a credit default swap option.

nodes.name: FxFixingDate
nodes.documentation: A type that is extending the Offset structure for providing the ability to specify an FX fixing date as an offset to dates specified somewhere else in the document.

nodes.name: LegAmount
nodes.documentation: A type describing the amount that will paid or received on each of the payment dates. This type is used to define both the Equity Amount and the Interest Amount.

nodes.name: specifiedPrice
nodes.documentation: The Specified Price in respect of a Transaction and a Commodity Reference Price.

nodes.name: Commission
nodes.documentation: A type describing the commission that will be charged for each of the hedge transactions.

nodes.name: MarketDisruption
nodes.documentation: Defines the handling of an averaging date market disruption for an equity derivative transaction.

nodes.name: Routing
nodes.documentation: A type that provides three alternative ways of identifying a party involved in the routing of a payment. The identification may use payment system identifiers only; actual name, address and other reference information; or a combination of both.

nodes.name: weeklyRollConvention
nodes.documentation: The specification of a weekly roll day.

nodes.name: CommodityBullionSettlementDisruptionEnum
nodes.documentation: The consequences of Bullion Settlement Disruption Events.

nodes.name: methodOfAdjustment
nodes.documentation: Defines how adjustments will be made to the contract should one or more of the extraordinary events occur.

nodes.name: FixedPaymentLeg
nodes.documentation: Fixed Payment Leg of a Dividend Swap.

nodes.name: RequestMessageHeader
nodes.documentation: A type refining the generic message header content to make it specific to request messages.

nodes.name: ReturnLeg
nodes.documentation: A type describing the return leg of a return type swap.

nodes.name: PricingModel
nodes.documentation: A scheme identifying the types of pricing model used to evaluate the price of an asset. Examples include Intrinsic, ClosedForm, MonteCarlo, BackwardInduction.

nodes.name: lowerBarrier
nodes.documentation: A type defining a number specified as non negative decimal greater than 0 inclusive.

nodes.name: CommodityBusinessCalendar
nodes.documentation: Defines a commodity business day calendar.

nodes.name: dividendComposition
nodes.documentation: Defines how the composition of dividends is to be determined.

nodes.name: fPVFinalPriceElectionFallback
nodes.documentation: Specifies the fallback provisions in respect to the applicable Futures Price Valuation.

nodes.name: RoundingDirectionEnum
nodes.documentation: The method of rounding a fractional number.

nodes.name: Quanto
nodes.documentation: Determines the currency rate that the seller of the equity amounts will apply at each valuation date for converting the respective amounts into a currency that is different from the currency denomination of the underlyer.

nodes.name: Collateral
nodes.documentation: A type for defining the obligations of the counterparty subject to credit support requirements.

nodes.name: SupervisoryBody
nodes.documentation: An identifier of an organization that supervises or regulates trading activity, e.g. CFTC, SEC, FSA, ODRF, etc.

nodes.name: PrincipalExchangeFeatures
nodes.documentation: A type describing the principal exchange features of the return swap.

nodes.name: CorrelationSwap
nodes.documentation: A Correlation Swap modelled using a single netted leg.

nodes.name: Future
nodes.documentation: An exchange traded future contract.

nodes.name: PaymentDates
nodes.documentation: A type defining parameters used to generate the payment dates schedule, including the specification of early or delayed payments. Payment dates are determined relative to the calculation period dates or the reset dates.

nodes.name: NonCashDividendTreatmentEnum
nodes.documentation: Defines treatment of non-cash dividends.

nodes.name: CommodityCalculationPeriodsSchedule
nodes.documentation: A parametric representation of the Calculation Periods for on Asian option or a leg of a swap. In case the calculation frequency is of value T (term), the period is defined by the commoditySwap\effectiveDate and the commoditySwap\terminationDate.

nodes.name: OptionalEarlyTermination
nodes.documentation: A type defining an early termination provision where either or both parties have the right to exercise.

nodes.name: RequestClearing
nodes.documentation: A message requesting that a trade be cleared by a clearing service.

nodes.name: optionType
nodes.documentation: Specifies an additional Forward type.

nodes.name: SensitivitySetDefinition
nodes.documentation: A sensitivity report definition, consisting of a collection of sensitivity definitions.

nodes.name: OptionFeatures
nodes.documentation: A type for defining option features.

nodes.name: IdentifiedPayerReceiver
nodes.documentation: A type extending the PayerReceiverEnum type wih an id attribute.

nodes.name: abandonmentOfScheme
nodes.documentation: Upon the occurrence of an Abandonment of Scheme, as defined in clause (h)(iv) of the Emissions Annex, one of the following elections, the specific terms of which are set forth in clause (b)(iii) of the Emissions Annex, will govern the parties rights and obligations with respect to this Emissions Transaction. If none of the above options is selected, Option A(1) will apply.

nodes.name: CompoundingFrequency
nodes.documentation: The frequency at which a rate is compounded.

nodes.name: LegalEntityReference
nodes.documentation: References a credit entity defined elsewhere in the document.

nodes.name: AmountSchedule
nodes.documentation: A type defining a currency amount or a currency amount schedule.

nodes.name: Return
nodes.documentation: A type describing the dividend return conditions applicable to the swap.

nodes.name: DividendPeriod
nodes.documentation: Abstract base class of all time bounded dividend period types.

nodes.name: RoutingIdsAndExplicitDetails
nodes.documentation: A type that provides a combination of payment system identification codes with physical postal address details, for the purposes of identifying a party involved in the routing of a payment.

nodes.name: AssetMeasureType
nodes.documentation: A scheme identifying the types of measures that can be used to describe an asset.

nodes.name: PartialExercise
nodes.documentation: A type defining partial exercise. As defined in the 2000 ISDA Definitions, Section 12.3 Partial Exercise, the buyer of the option may exercise all or less than all the notional amount of the underlying swap but may not be less than the minimum notional amount (if specified) and must be an integral multiple of the integral multiple amount if specified.

nodes.name: FeeElectionEnum
nodes.documentation: Defines the fee type.

nodes.name: realisedVarianceMethod
nodes.documentation: The contract specifies whether which price must satisfy the boundary condition.

nodes.name: CalculationAgent
nodes.documentation: A type defining the ISDA calculation agent responsible for performing duties as defined in the applicable product definitions.

nodes.name: ExtendibleProvision
nodes.documentation: A type defining an option to extend an existing swap transaction on the specified exercise dates for a term ending on the specified new termination date.

nodes.name: Mortgage
nodes.documentation: A type describing a mortgage asset.

nodes.name: Composite
nodes.documentation: Specifies the conditions to be applied for converting into a reference currency when the actual currency rate is not determined upfront.

nodes.name: StandardSettlementStyleEnum
nodes.documentation: The code specification of whether a trade is settling using standard settlement instructions as well as whether it is a candidate for settlement netting.

nodes.name: PartyRelationshipDocumentation
nodes.documentation: A description of the legal agreement(s) and definitions that document a party's relationships with other parties

nodes.name: CommodityPhysicalQuantityBase
nodes.documentation: A type defining the physical quantity of the commodity to be delivered.

nodes.name: Formula
nodes.documentation: A type describing a financial formula, with its description and components.

nodes.name: CashPriceMethod
nodes.documentation: A type defining the parameters necessary for each of the ISDA cash price methods for cash settlement.

nodes.name: PeriodExtendedEnum
nodes.documentation: The specification of a time period containing additional values such as Term.

nodes.name: PrevailingTime
nodes.documentation: A type for defining a time with respect to a geographic location, for example 11:00 Phoenix, USA. This type should be used where a wider range of locations than those available as business centres is required.

nodes.name: InstrumentTradePrincipal
nodes.documentation: A structure describing the value in "native" currency of an instrument that was traded.

nodes.name: CommodityStrikeSchedule
nodes.documentation: The Strike Price per Unit per Calculation Period. There must be a Strike Price per Unit step specified for each Calculation Period, regardless of whether the Strike changes or remains the same between periods.

nodes.name: EntityType
nodes.documentation: Defines a coding scheme of the entity types defined in the ISDA First to Default documentation.

nodes.name: ReturnSwapPaymentDates
nodes.documentation: A type describing the return payment dates of the swap.

nodes.name: settlementDisruption
nodes.documentation: The consequences of Bullion Settlement Disruption Events.

nodes.name: EventIdentifier
nodes.documentation: Identification of a business event, for example through its correlation id or a business identifier.

nodes.name: InterestRateStreamReference
nodes.documentation: Reference to an InterestRateStream component.

nodes.name: Address
nodes.documentation: A type that represents a physical postal address.

nodes.name: settlementType
nodes.documentation: Shows how the transaction is to be settled when it is exercised.

nodes.name: CommodityFrequencyType
nodes.documentation: Frequency Type for use in Pricing Date specifications.

nodes.name: FloatingRateDefinition
nodes.documentation: A type defining parameters associated with a floating rate reset. This type forms part of the cashflows representation of a stream.

nodes.name: ReferenceBank
nodes.documentation: A type to describe an institution (party) identified by means of a coding scheme and an optional name.

nodes.name: BreakageCostEnum
nodes.documentation: When breakage cost is applicable, defines who is calculating it.

nodes.name: ObligationCategoryEnum
nodes.documentation: Used in both the obligations and deliverable obligations of the credit default swap to represent a class or type of securities which apply.

nodes.name: SwapAdditionalTerms
nodes.documentation: Additional terms to a swap contract.

nodes.name: VolatilityRepresentation
nodes.documentation: A representation of volatilities of an asset. This is a generic structure whose values can be supplied in a specific volatility matrix.

nodes.name: ElectricityDeliverySystemFirm
nodes.documentation: The physical delivery obligation options specific to a system firm transaction.

nodes.name: CorrelationLeg
nodes.documentation: A type describing return which is driven by a Correlation calculation.

nodes.name: ReturnSwapNotional
nodes.documentation: Specifies the notional of return type swap. When used in the equity leg, the definition will typically combine the actual amount (using the notional component defined by the FpML industry group) and the determination method. When used in the interest leg, the definition will typically point to the definition of the equity leg.

nodes.name: RequestExecution
nodes.documentation: A message requesting that an order be executed.

nodes.name: CreditDocument
nodes.documentation: A credit arrangement used in support of swaps trading.

nodes.name: negativeInterestRateTreatment
nodes.documentation: The method of calculating payment obligations when a floating rate is negative (either due to a quoted negative floating rate or by operation of a spread that is subtracted from the floating rate).

nodes.name: PremiumQuote
nodes.documentation: A type that describes the option premium as quoted.

nodes.name: ConfirmationStatus
nodes.documentation: Message for sending matching results. Response message that returns the status of an event that have been submitted for matching.

nodes.name: ForwardRateCurve
nodes.documentation: A curve used to model a set of forward interest rates. Used for forecasting interest rates as part of a pricing calculation.

nodes.name: WeatherCalculationPeriods
nodes.documentation: The schedule of Calculation Period First Days and Lasts Days. If there is only one First Day - Last Day pair then the First is equal to the Effective Date and the Last Day is equal to the Termination Date.

nodes.name: TradeProcessingTimestamps
nodes.documentation: Allows timing information about when a trade was processed and reported to be recorded.

nodes.name: ResponseMessageHeader
nodes.documentation: A type refining the generic message header to make it specific to response messages.

nodes.name: WeightedPartialDerivative
nodes.documentation: A partial derivative multiplied by a weighting factor.

nodes.name: period
nodes.documentation: The specification of a time period

nodes.name: CashSettlementReferenceBanks
nodes.documentation: A type defining the list of reference institutions polled for relevant rates or prices when determining the cash settlement amount for a product where cash settlement is applicable.

nodes.name: indexCancellation
nodes.documentation: The specification of the consequences of Index Events.

nodes.name: CommodityMetalBrandName
nodes.documentation: The name of the entity that issues the brand

nodes.name: ValuationReference
nodes.documentation: Reference to a Valuation or any derived structure such as PricingStructureValuation.

nodes.name: DerivativeFormula
nodes.documentation: A formula for computing a complex derivative from partial derivatives. Its value is the sum of the terms divided by the product of the denominator terms.

nodes.name: indexModification
nodes.documentation: The specification of the consequences of Index Events.

nodes.name: ConstituentWeight
nodes.documentation: A type describing the weight of each of the underlyer constituent within the basket, either in absolute or relative terms.

nodes.name: FxRate
nodes.documentation: A type describing the rate of a currency conversion: pair of currency, quotation mode and exchange rate.

nodes.name: PersonRole
nodes.documentation: A type describing a role played by a person in one or more transactions. Examples include roles such as Trader, Broker, MiddleOffice, Legal, etc. This can be extended to provide custom roles.

nodes.name: IdentifiedRate
nodes.documentation: A rate which can be referenced elsewhere.

nodes.name: IntermediaryInformation
nodes.documentation: A type that describes the information to identify an intermediary through which payment will be made by the correspondent bank to the ultimate beneficiary of the funds.

nodes.name: ReturnSwapNotionalAmountReference
nodes.documentation: A reference to the return swap notional amount.

nodes.name: rateObservationQuoteBasis
nodes.documentation: The specification of how an FX OTC option strike price is quoted.

nodes.name: ImplementationSpecification
nodes.documentation: A version of a specification document used by the message generator to format the document.

nodes.name: WeatherStationWMO
nodes.documentation: A code identifying a Weather Index WMO.

nodes.name: TradeCategory
nodes.documentation: A scheme used to categorize positions.

nodes.name: EquityAmericanExercise
nodes.documentation: A type for defining exercise procedures associated with an American style exercise of an equity option. This entity inherits from the type SharedAmericanExercise.

nodes.name: BoundedCorrelation
nodes.documentation: A type describing correlation bounds, which form a cap and a floor on the realized correlation.

nodes.name: RollConventionEnum
nodes.documentation: The convention for determining the sequence of calculation period end dates. It is used in conjunction with a specified frequency and the regular period start date of a calculation period, e.g. semi-annual IMM roll dates.

nodes.name: differenceSeverity
nodes.documentation: The ISDA defined value indicating the severity of a difference.

nodes.name: MimeType
nodes.documentation: The type that indicates the type of media used to store the content. MimeType is used to determine the software product(s) that can read the content. MIME types are described in RFC 2046.

nodes.name: MortgageSector
nodes.documentation: A type describing the typology of mortgage obligations.

nodes.name: FxAsianFeature
nodes.documentation: Descibes the averaging period properties for an asian option.

nodes.name: EntityId
nodes.documentation: A legal entity identifier (e.g. RED entity code).

nodes.name: Material
nodes.documentation: A scheme identifying the types of metal product for a physically settled metal trade.

nodes.name: ContractId
nodes.documentation: A contact id identifier allocated by a party. FpML does not define the domain values associated with this element.

nodes.name: MultiDimensionalPricingData
nodes.documentation: A pricing data set that contains a series of points with coordinates. It is a sparse matrix representation of a multi-dimensional matrix.

nodes.name: OffsetPrevailingTime
nodes.documentation: Allows the specification of a time that may be on a day prior or subsequent to the day in question. This type is intended for use with a day of the week (i.e. where no actual date is specified) as part of, for example, a period that runs from 23:00-07:00 on a series of days and where holidays on the actual days would affect the entire time period.

nodes.name: EquitySwapTransactionSupplement
nodes.documentation: A type for defining Equity Swap Transaction Supplement

nodes.name: title
nodes.documentation: Describes how and when title to the commodity transfers.

nodes.name: FxTrigger
nodes.documentation: Describes an FX trigger condition.

nodes.name: Barrier
nodes.documentation: As per ISDA 2002 Definitions.

nodes.name: ReturnTypeEnum
nodes.documentation: The type of return associated with the equity swap.

nodes.name: CommodityMarketDisruption
nodes.documentation: ISDA 1993 or 2005 commodity market disruption elements.

nodes.name: FraDiscountingEnum
nodes.documentation: The method of FRA discounting, if any, that will apply.

nodes.name: BusinessUnitRole
nodes.documentation: A type describing a role played by a unit in one or more transactions. Examples include roles such as Trader, Collateral, Confirmation, Settlement, etc. This can be extended to provide custom roles.

nodes.name: CalculationAgentPartyEnum
nodes.documentation: The specification of how a calculation agent will be determined.

nodes.name: resetRelativeTo
nodes.documentation: The specification of whether resets occur relative to the first or last day of a calculation period.

nodes.name: StubCalculationPeriod
nodes.documentation: A type describing the Stub Calculation Period.

nodes.name: CorrelationId
nodes.documentation: A type defining a correlation identifier and qualifying scheme

nodes.name: quotationStyle
nodes.documentation: Indicates the actual quotation style of of PointsUpFront or TradedSpread that was used to quote this trade.

nodes.name: GasProduct
nodes.documentation: A type defining the characteristics of the gas being traded in a physically settled gas transaction.

nodes.name: dividendEntitlement
nodes.documentation: The date on which the receiver of the equity return is entitled to the dividend.

nodes.name: CreditDefaultSwapOption
nodes.documentation: A complex type to support the credit default swap option.

nodes.name: UnderlyingAsset
nodes.documentation: An exchange traded bond.

nodes.name: valuationMethod
nodes.documentation: The ISDA defined methodology for determining the final price of the reference obligation for purposes of cash settlement.

nodes.name: FxOption
nodes.documentation: Describes an FX option with optional asian and barrier features.

nodes.name: originatingEvent
nodes.documentation: A type used to report how a position originated.

nodes.name: ValuationMethodEnum
nodes.documentation: The ISDA defined methodology for determining the final price of the reference obligation for purposes of cash settlement.

nodes.name: Language
nodes.documentation: The data type used for indicating the language of the resource, described using the ISO 639-2/T Code.

nodes.name: CalendarSourceEnum
nodes.documentation: Describes the date source calendar for a contract whereby the prices are from the underlying commodity price source (e.g. exchange traded futures contract), but the dates are based off another calendar (e.g. the listed option on the futures contract).

nodes.name: ServiceProcessingStatus
nodes.documentation: A type defining the content model for report on the status of the processing by a service. In the future we may wish to provide some kind of scope or other qualification for the event, e.g. the currencies, products, or books to which it applies.

nodes.name: bullionType
nodes.documentation: Defines which type of bullion is applicable for a Bullion Transaction.

nodes.name: FixedPrice
nodes.documentation: A type defining the Fixed Price.

nodes.name: ScheduledDateType
nodes.documentation: A scheme used to identify the type of a stream scheduled servicing date.

nodes.name: CommodityExpireRelativeToEvent
nodes.documentation: A scheme identifying the physical event relative to which option expiration occurs.

nodes.name: PaymentCalculationPeriod
nodes.documentation: A type defining the adjusted payment date and associated calculation period parameters required to calculate the actual or projected payment amount. This type forms part of the cashflow representation of a swap stream.

nodes.name: MarketReference
nodes.documentation: Reference to a market structure.

nodes.name: TelephoneNumber
nodes.documentation: A type that represents a telephonic contact.

nodes.name: volatilityStrikePrice
nodes.documentation: A type defining a number specified as non negative decimal greater than 0 inclusive.

nodes.name: ContractualSupplement
nodes.documentation: A contractual supplement (such as those published by ISDA) that will apply to the trade.

nodes.name: PricingInputType
nodes.documentation: The type of pricing structure represented.

nodes.name: Exercise
nodes.documentation: A type defining the exercise period for an American style option together with any rules governing the notional amount of the underlying which can be exercised on any given exercise date and any associated exercise fees.

nodes.name: ExchangeId
nodes.documentation: A short form unique identifier for an exchange. If the element is not present then the exchange shall be the primary exchange on which the underlying is listed. The term "Exchange" is assumed to have the meaning as defined in the ISDA 2002 Equity Derivatives Definitions.

nodes.name: ClearingStatusItem
nodes.documentation: A component of a clearing status report. This provides the clearing status for a single trade.

nodes.name: PartyTradeIdentifier
nodes.documentation: A type defining one or more trade identifiers allocated to the trade by a party. A link identifier allows the trade to be associated with other related trades, e.g. trades forming part of a larger structured transaction. It is expected that for external communication of trade there will be only one tradeId sent in the document per party.

nodes.name: QueryParameterOperator
nodes.documentation: A type representing an operator describing the relationship of a value to its corresponding identifier for a parameter describing a query portfolio. Possible relationships include equals, not equals, less than, greater than. Possible operators are listed in the queryParameterOperatorScheme.

nodes.name: PrincipalExchangeAmount
nodes.documentation: Specifies the principal exchange amount, either by explicitly defining it, or by point to an amount defined somewhere else in the swap document.

nodes.name: varianceStrikePrice
nodes.documentation: A type defining a number specified as non negative decimal greater than 0 inclusive.

nodes.name: TradeAmendmentContent
nodes.documentation: A structure describing a negotiated amendment.

nodes.name: VersionedTradeId
nodes.documentation: Trade Id with Version Support

nodes.name: PositionConstituent
nodes.documentation: The items (trades, trade references, holdings, other positions) that comprise this position. Currently a position may consist only of a single trade, a reference to a previously submitted position, or a reference to the trade. The choice structure is optional to allow extensions to be placed within this container.

nodes.name: ExerciseFee
nodes.documentation: A type defining the fee payable on exercise of an option. This fee may be defined as an amount or a percentage of the notional exercised.

nodes.name: FloatingRate
nodes.documentation: A type defining a floating rate.

nodes.name: VerificationMethod
nodes.documentation: A type used to represent the type of mechanism that can be used to verify a trade.

nodes.name: GoverningLaw
nodes.documentation: Identification of the law governing the transaction.

nodes.name: BermudaExercise
nodes.documentation: A type defining the Bermuda option exercise dates and the expiration date together with any rules govenerning the notional amount of the underlying which can be exercised on any given exercise date and any associated exercise fee.

nodes.name: BoundedVariance
nodes.documentation: A type describing variance bounds, which are used to exclude money price values outside of the specified range In a Up Conditional Swap Underlyer price must be equal to or higher than Lower Barrier In a Down Conditional Swap Underlyer price must be equal to or lower than Upper Barrier In a Corridor Conditional Swap Underlyer price must be equal to or higher than Lower Barrier and must be equal to or lower than Upper Barrier.

nodes.name: BondOptionStrike
nodes.documentation: A complex type to specify the strike of a bond or convertible bond option.

nodes.name: premiumType
nodes.documentation: Premium Type for Forward Start Equity Option

nodes.name: ReferenceSwapCurve
nodes.documentation: A complex type used to specify the option and convertible bond option strike when expressed in reference to a swap curve.

nodes.name: Market
nodes.documentation: A collection of pricing inputs.

nodes.name: CashflowId
nodes.documentation: An identifier used to identify a single component cashflow.

nodes.name: ClearingStatusValue
nodes.documentation: The current status value of a clearing request.

nodes.name: CreditEventNoticeDocument
nodes.documentation: An event type that records the occurrence of a credit event notice.

nodes.name: stepValue
nodes.documentation: A type defining a number specified as non negative decimal greater than 0 inclusive.

nodes.name: RestrictedPercentage
nodes.documentation: A type defining a percentage specified as decimal from 0 to 1. A percentage of 5% would be represented as 0.05.

nodes.name: EquityMultipleExercise
nodes.documentation: A type for defining the multiple exercise provisions of an American or Bermuda style equity option.

nodes.name: CoalProductSpecifications
nodes.documentation: The different options for specifying the quality attributes of the coal to be delivered.

nodes.name: MakeWholeProvisions
nodes.documentation: A type to hold early exercise provisions.

nodes.name: CreditRating
nodes.documentation: A party's credit rating.

nodes.name: interpolationPeriod
nodes.documentation: Defines applicable periods for interpolation.

nodes.name: limitationPercentage
nodes.documentation: A type defining a percentage specified as decimal from 0 to 1. A percentage of 5% would be represented as 0.05.

nodes.name: ExecutionDateTime
nodes.documentation: A type defining the trade execution date time and the source of it. For use inside containing types which already have a Reference to a Party that has assigned this trade execution date time.

nodes.name: hourMinuteTime
nodes.documentation: A type defining a time specified in hh:mm:ss format where the second component must be '00', e.g. 11am would be represented as 11:00:00.

nodes.name: AdjustableDates
nodes.documentation: A type for defining a series of dates that shall be subject to adjustment if they would otherwise fall on a day that is not a business day in the specified business centers, together with the convention for adjusting the dates.

nodes.name: CalendarSpread
nodes.documentation: A type for defining a calendar spread feature.

nodes.name: PositiveStep
nodes.documentation: A type defining a step date and strictly-positive step value pair. This step definitions are used to define varying rate or amount schedules, e.g. a notional amortization or a step-up coupon schedule.

nodes.name: IdentifiedCurrencyReference
nodes.documentation: Reference to a currency with ID attribute

nodes.name: StandardProduct
nodes.documentation: Simple product representation providing key information about a variety of different products. Standard products - for use in Transparency reporting to define a product that represents a standardized OTC derivative transaction whose economics do not need to be fully described using an FpML schema because they are implied by the product ID. In other views, standard products are present for convenience to support internal messaging and workflows that are cross-product. Standard products are not full trade representations as such they are not intended to be used for confirming trades.

nodes.name: PartyRoleType
nodes.documentation: A type refining the role a role played by a party in one or more transactions. Examples include "AllPositions" and "SomePositions" for Guarantor. This can be extended to provide custom types.

nodes.name: CreditCurveValuation
nodes.documentation: A set of credit curve values, which can include pricing inputs (which are typically credit spreads), default probabilities, and recovery rates.

nodes.name: MaturityNotification
nodes.documentation: A message used to notify another party that a trade has matured. This can be used to report, for example, that a swap has passed its final payment and can be removed, or that an option has expired without being executed.

nodes.name: CommodityPhysicalExercise
nodes.documentation: The parameters for defining how the physically-settled commodity option can be exercised and how it is settled.

nodes.name: ProposedCollateralAllocation
nodes.documentation: The proposed collateral allocation.

nodes.name: integralMultipleExercise
nodes.documentation: A type defining a number specified as positive decimal greater than 0 exclusive.

nodes.name: ReportingRoles
nodes.documentation: The roles of the parties in reporting information such as positions.

nodes.name: TimeDimension
nodes.documentation: The time dimensions of a term-structure. The user must supply either a tenor or a date or both.

nodes.name: BasketReferenceInformation
nodes.documentation: CDS Basket Reference Information

nodes.name: ResetFrequency
nodes.documentation: A type defining the reset frequency. In the case of a weekly reset, also specifies the day of the week that the reset occurs. If the reset frequency is greater than the calculation period frequency the this implies that more or more reset dates is established for each calculation period and some form of rate averaginhg is applicable. The specific averaging method of calculation is specified in FloatingRateCalculation. In case the reset frequency is of value T (term), the period is defined by the swap\swapStream\calculationPerioDates\effectiveDate and the swap\swapStream\calculationPerioDates\terminationDate.

nodes.name: PrincipalExchangeDescriptions
nodes.documentation: Specifies each of the characteristics of the principal exchange cashflows, in terms of paying/receiving counterparties, amounts and dates.

nodes.name: standardSettlementStyle
nodes.documentation: The code specification of whether a trade is settling using standard settlement instructions as well as whether it is a candidate for settlement netting.

nodes.name: DividendDateReferenceEnum
nodes.documentation: The reference to a dividend date.

nodes.name: RequestClearingRetracted
nodes.documentation: A message withdrawing a request that a trade be cleared by a clearing service.

nodes.name: InstrumentTradeQuantity
nodes.documentation: A structure describing the amount of an instrument that was traded.

nodes.name: equityExpirationTimeType
nodes.documentation: Defines points in the day when equity option exercise and valuation can occur.

nodes.name: DateRelativeToPaymentDates
nodes.documentation: A type to provide the ability to point to multiple payment nodes in the document through the unbounded paymentDatesReference.

nodes.name: NonCorrectableRequestMessage
nodes.documentation: A type defining the content model for a request message that cannot be subsequently corrected or retracted.

nodes.name: PricingParameterDerivativeReference
nodes.documentation: Reference to a partial derivative.

nodes.name: TimestampTypeScheme
nodes.documentation: The type or meaning of a timestamp.

nodes.name: BasketConstituent
nodes.documentation: A type describing each of the constituents of a basket.

nodes.name: MatchId
nodes.documentation: An identifier used to identify matched cashflows.

nodes.name: CommoditySettlementPeriodsNotionalQuantitySchedule
nodes.documentation: The notional quantity schedule of electricity that applies to one or more groups of Settlement Periods.

nodes.name: CoalQualityAdjustments
nodes.documentation: A scheme identifying the quality adjustment formulae for a physically settled coal trade.

nodes.name: DateList
nodes.documentation: List of Dates

nodes.name: QuotedAssetSet
nodes.documentation: A collection of quoted assets.

nodes.name: indexDisruption
nodes.documentation: The specification of the consequences of Index Events.

nodes.name: FloatingLegCalculation
nodes.documentation: A type to capture details relevant to the calculation of the floating price.

nodes.name: ReturnSwapLegUnderlyer
nodes.documentation: A type describing the return leg of a return type swap.

nodes.name: Variance
nodes.documentation: A type describing the variance amount of a variance swap.

nodes.name: Asian
nodes.documentation: As per ISDA 2002 Definitions.

nodes.name: CreditEventsReference
nodes.documentation: Reference to credit events.

nodes.name: FxOptionPremium
nodes.documentation: A type that specifies the premium exchanged for a single option trade or option strategy.

nodes.name: UnprocessedElementWrapper
nodes.documentation: A type holding a structure that is unvalidated

nodes.name: ElectricityDelivery
nodes.documentation: The physical delivery conditions for electricity.

nodes.name: Resource
nodes.documentation: Describes the resource that contains the media representation of a business event (i.e used for stating the Publicly Available Information). For example, can describe a file or a URL that represents the event. This type is an extended version of a type defined by RIXML (www.rixml.org).

nodes.name: IndexEventConsequenceEnum
nodes.documentation: The specification of the consequences of Index Events.

nodes.name: TradeReferenceInformation
nodes.documentation: Defines a type that allows trade identifiers and/or trade information to be represented for a trade.

nodes.name: CommodityForward
nodes.documentation: Commodity Forward

nodes.name: ServiceProcessingCycle
nodes.documentation: A type that can be used to describe the processing phase of a service. For example, EndOfDay, Intraday.

nodes.name: FxBarrierFeature
nodes.documentation: Describes the properties of an Fx barrier.

nodes.name: Position
nodes.documentation: A collection of related trades or positions and the corresponding aggregate exposures generated by these.

nodes.name: AveragingPeriod
nodes.documentation: Period over which an average value is taken.

nodes.name: AmericanExercise
nodes.documentation: A type defining the exercise period for an American style option together with any rules governing the notional amount of the underlying which can be exercised on any given exercise date and any associated exercise fees.

nodes.name: FixedPaymentAmount
nodes.documentation: Fixed payment amount within a Dividend Swap.

nodes.name: TransactionCharacteristic
nodes.documentation: A characteristic of a transaction used in declaring an end-user exception.

nodes.name: DateOffset
nodes.documentation: A type defining an offset used in calculating a date when this date is defined in reference to another date through a date offset. The type includes the convention for adjusting the date and an optional sequence element to indicate the order in a sequence of multiple date offsets.

nodes.name: FxStrikePrice
nodes.documentation: A type that describes the rate of exchange at which the option has been struck.

nodes.name: FxDigitalAmericanExercise
nodes.documentation: Describes the characteristics for american exercise of FX products.

nodes.name: AdjustableDate
nodes.documentation: A type for defining a date that shall be subject to adjustment if it would otherwise fall on a day that is not a business day in the specified business centers, together with the convention for adjusting the date.

nodes.name: CommodityInformationProvider
nodes.documentation: The publication in which the rate, price, index or factor is to be found. (e.g Gas Daily, Platts Bloomberg.)

nodes.name: EquityOptionTransactionSupplement
nodes.documentation: A type for defining equity option transaction supplements.

nodes.name: deliveryDates
nodes.documentation: In respect of a Transaction and a Commodity Reference Price, the relevant date or month for delivery of the underlying Commodity.

nodes.name: Sensitivity
nodes.documentation: The sensitivity of a value to a defined change in input parameters.

nodes.name: AnyAssetReference
nodes.documentation: A reference to an asset, e.g. a portfolio, trade, or reference instrument..

nodes.name: OptionBase
nodes.documentation: A complex type to support the credit default swap option.

nodes.name: priceExpression
nodes.documentation: The mode of expression of a price.

nodes.name: TriggerEvent
nodes.documentation: Observation point for trigger.

nodes.name: EquityOptionTypeEnum
nodes.documentation: Specifies an additional Forward type.

nodes.name: CurveInstrument
nodes.documentation: Abstract base class for instruments intended to be used primarily for building curves.

nodes.name: YieldCurveValuation
nodes.documentation: The values of a yield curve, including possibly inputs and outputs (dfs, forwards, zero rates).

nodes.name: CollateralizationType
nodes.documentation: Code that describes what type of collateral is posted by a party to a transaction. Options include Uncollateralized, Partial, Full, One-Way.

nodes.name: FxBarrierTypeEnum
nodes.documentation: The specification of whether a barrier within an FX OTC option is a knockin or knockout, as well as whether it is a standard barrier or a reverse barrier.

nodes.name: FxCurve
nodes.documentation: An fx curve object., which includes pricing inputs and term structures for fx forwards.

nodes.name: LoadTypeEnum
nodes.documentation: LoadType is a summary of the full description of the settlement periods with respect to the region. Used for describing Electricity delivery schedules.

nodes.name: BusinessCenterTime
nodes.documentation: A type for defining a time with respect to a business day calendar location. For example, 11:00am London time.

nodes.name: CommodityMultipleExercise
nodes.documentation: A type for defining the multiple exercise provisions of an American style commodity option.

nodes.name: ValuationScenarioReference
nodes.documentation: Reference to a valuation scenario.

nodes.name: ProtectionTermsReference
nodes.documentation: Reference to protectionTerms component.

nodes.name: declaredCashEquivalentDividendPercentage
nodes.documentation: A type defining a number specified as non negative decimal greater than 0 inclusive.

nodes.name: NotionalAdjustmentEnum
nodes.documentation: The conditions that govern the adjustment to the number of units of the equity swap.

nodes.name: PrePayment
nodes.documentation: A type for defining PrePayment.

nodes.name: ExecutionAdviceRetracted
nodes.documentation: A message that withdraws an advice to a third party that a trade execution has occurred.

nodes.name: stepRelativeTo
nodes.documentation: The specification of whether a percentage rate change, used to calculate a change in notional outstanding, is expressed as a percentage of the initial notional amount or the previously outstanding notional amount.

nodes.name: PartyTradeInformation
nodes.documentation: A type defining party-specific additional information that may be recorded against a trade.

nodes.name: Math
nodes.documentation: A type defining a mathematical expression.

nodes.name: MoneyReference
nodes.documentation: References a Money instance.

nodes.name: CommodityFxType
nodes.documentation: Identifes how the FX rate will be applied. This is intended to differentiate between the various methods for applying FX to the floating price such as a daily calculation, or averaging the FX and applying the average at the end of each CalculationPeriod.

nodes.name: IdentifiedAsset
nodes.documentation: An exchange traded bond.

nodes.name: FxAmericanExercise
nodes.documentation: Describes the characteristics for american exercise of FX products.

nodes.name: ReturnSwapEarlyTermination
nodes.documentation: A type describing the date from which each of the party may be allowed to terminate the trade.

nodes.name: RelativeDateOffset
nodes.documentation: A type defining a date (referred to as the derived date) as a relative offset from another date (referred to as the anchor date) plus optional date adjustments.

nodes.name: declaredCashDividendPercentage
nodes.documentation: A type defining a number specified as non negative decimal greater than 0 inclusive.

nodes.name: ServiceNotification
nodes.documentation: A type defining the content model for a message that allows a service to send a notification message to a user of the service.

nodes.name: Leg
nodes.documentation: A supertype of leg. All swap legs extend this type.

nodes.name: ExchangeRate
nodes.documentation: A type that is used for describing the exchange rate for a particular transaction.

nodes.name: CommodityExercise
nodes.documentation: The parameters for defining how the commodity option can be exercised, how it is priced and how it is settled.

nodes.name: Stub
nodes.documentation: A type defining how a stub calculation period amount is calculated and the start and end date of the stub. A single floating rate tenor different to that used for the regular part of the calculation periods schedule may be specified, or two floating rate tenors many be specified. If two floating rate tenors are specified then Linear Interpolation (in accordance with the 2000 ISDA Definitions, Section 8.3 Interpolation) is assumed to apply. Alternatively, an actual known stub rate or stub amount may be specified.

nodes.name: RateObservation
nodes.documentation: A type defining parameters associated with an individual observation or fixing. This type forms part of the cashflow representation of a stream.

nodes.name: SingleUnderlyer
nodes.documentation: A type describing a single underlyer

nodes.name: InterestMethodEnum
nodes.documentation: The type of method.

nodes.name: TriggerTypeEnum
nodes.documentation: The specification of whether an option would trigger or expire depending upon whether the spot rate is above or below the barrier rate.

nodes.name: AdjustableOrRelativeDates
nodes.documentation: A type giving the choice between defining a series of dates as an explicit list of dates together with applicable adjustments or as relative to some other series of (anchor) dates.

nodes.name: ZeroRateCurve
nodes.documentation: A curve used to model a set of zero-coupon interest rates.

nodes.name: differenceType
nodes.documentation: The ISDA defined value indicating the nature of a difference.

nodes.name: ResetDates
nodes.documentation: A type defining the parameters used to generate the reset dates schedule and associated fixing dates. The reset dates are determined relative to the calculation periods schedules dates.

nodes.name: NonNegativePayment
nodes.documentation: A complex type to specify non negative payments.

nodes.name: AdditionalEvent
nodes.documentation: Abstract base type for an extension/substitution point to customize FpML and add additional events.

nodes.name: InterestCalculation
nodes.documentation: Specifies the calculation method of the interest rate leg of the return swap. Includes the floating or fixed rate calculation definitions, along with the determination of the day count fraction.

nodes.name: BullionDeliveryLocation
nodes.documentation: A scheme defining where bullion is to be delivered for a Bullion Transaction.

nodes.name: TradeChangeContent
nodes.documentation: A structure describing a non-negotiated trade resulting from a market event.

nodes.name: CoalDelivery
nodes.documentation: The physical delivery conditions for coal.

nodes.name: ElectricityDeliveryFirm
nodes.documentation: The physical delivery obligation options specific to a firm transaction.

nodes.name: MandatoryEarlyTermination
nodes.documentation: A type to define an early termination provision for which exercise is mandatory.

nodes.name: FxBoundary
nodes.documentation: Describes a precise boundary value.

nodes.name: Validation
nodes.documentation: A reference identifying a rule within a validation scheme.

nodes.name: FacilityType
nodes.documentation: A type describing the type of loan facility.

nodes.name: PositiveDecimal
nodes.documentation: A type defining a number specified as positive decimal greater than 0 exclusive.

nodes.name: FxMultipleExercise
nodes.documentation: Describes the limits on the size of notional when multiple exercise is allowed.

nodes.name: PartyRole
nodes.documentation: A type describing a role played by a party in one or more transactions. Examples include roles such as guarantor, custodian, confirmation service provider, etc. This can be extended to provide custom roles.

nodes.name: CreditEventNotification
nodes.documentation: A message type defining the ISDA defined Credit Event Notice. ISDA defines it as an irrevocable notice from a Notifying Party to the other party that describes a Credit Event that occurred. A Credit Event Notice must contain detail of the facts relevant to the determination that a Credit Event has occurred.

nodes.name: rate
nodes.documentation: A type defining a number specified as positive decimal greater than 0 exclusive.

nodes.name: NotificationMessage
nodes.documentation: A type defining the basic content for a message sent to inform another system that some 'business event' has occured. Notifications are not expected to be replied to.

nodes.name: StubCalculationPeriodAmount
nodes.documentation: A type defining how the initial or final stub calculation period amounts is calculated. For example, the rate to be applied to the initial or final stub calculation period may be the linear interpolation of two different tenors for the floating rate index specified in the calculation period amount component, e.g. A two month stub period may used the linear interpolation of a one month and three month floating rate. The different rate tenors would be specified in this component. Note that a maximum of two rate tenors can be specified. If a stub period uses a single index tenor and this is the same as that specified in the calculation period amount component then the initial stub or final stub component, as the case may be, must not be included.

nodes.name: ReturnSwapAmount
nodes.documentation: Specifies, in relation to each Payment Date, the amount to which the Payment Date relates. For Equity Swaps this element is equivalent to the Equity Amount term as defined in the ISDA 2002 Equity Derivatives Definitions.

nodes.name: MarketDisruptionEvent
nodes.documentation: A Market Disruption Event.

nodes.name: TermDeposit
nodes.documentation: A class defining the content model for a term deposit product.

nodes.name: compoundingMethod
nodes.documentation: The compounding calculation method

nodes.name: maximumExclusive
nodes.documentation: A type defining a number specified as positive decimal greater than 0 exclusive.

nodes.name: FxLinkedNotionalAmount
nodes.documentation: A type to describe the cashflow representation for fx linked notionals.

nodes.name: ChangeEvent
nodes.documentation: Abstract base type for non-negotiated trade change descriptions

nodes.name: Schedule
nodes.documentation: A type defining a currency amount or a currency amount schedule.

nodes.name: breakFeeRate
nodes.documentation: A type defining a number specified as non negative decimal greater than 0 inclusive.

nodes.name: Period
nodes.documentation: A type defining a date (referred to as the derived date) as a relative offset from another date (referred to as the anchor date) plus optional date adjustments.

nodes.name: CommodityPayRelativeToEnum
nodes.documentation: The Commodity specification of whether payments occur relative e.g. to the Trade Date, or the end of the month, etc.

nodes.name: Offset
nodes.documentation: A type defining a date (referred to as the derived date) as a relative offset from another date (referred to as the anchor date) plus optional date adjustments.

nodes.name: MultipleExercise
nodes.documentation: A type defining multiple exercises. As defining in the 2000 ISDA Definitions, Section 12.4. Multiple Exercise, the buyer of the option has the right to exercise all or less than all the unexercised notional amount of the underlying swap on one or more days in the exercise period, but on any such day may not exercise less than the minimum notional amount or more than the maximum notional amount, and if an integral multiple amount is specified, the notional exercised must be equal to or, be an integral multiple of, the integral multiple amount.

nodes.name: minimumNumberOfOptions
nodes.documentation: A type defining a number specified as non negative decimal greater than 0 inclusive.

nodes.name: CancelableProvisionAdjustedDates
nodes.documentation: A type to define the adjusted dates for a cancelable provision on a swap transaction.

nodes.name: MessageAddress
nodes.documentation: The data type used for identifying a message address.

nodes.name: SharedAmericanExercise
nodes.documentation: TBA

nodes.name: SupervisorRegistration
nodes.documentation: Provides information about a regulator or other supervisory body that an organization is registered with.

nodes.name: basketPercentage
nodes.documentation: A type defining a percentage specified as decimal from 0 to 1. A percentage of 5% would be represented as 0.05.

nodes.name: calorificValue
nodes.documentation: A type defining a number specified as non negative decimal greater than 0 inclusive.

nodes.name: AdditionalPaymentAmount
nodes.documentation: Specifies the amount of the fee along with, when applicable, the formula that supports its determination.

nodes.name: CashflowType
nodes.documentation: A coding scheme used to describe the type or purpose of a cash flow or cash flow component.

nodes.name: CoalStandardQualitySchedule
nodes.documentation: The quality attributes of the coal to be delivered, specified on a periodic basis.

nodes.name: LagReference
nodes.documentation: Allows a lag to reference one already defined elsewhere in the trade.

nodes.name: NonNegativeStep
nodes.documentation: A type defining a step date and non-negative step value pair. This step definitions are used to define varying rate or amount schedules, e.g. a notional amortization or a step-up coupon schedule.

nodes.name: PricingStructurePoint
nodes.documentation: A single valued point with a set of coordinates that define an arbitrary number of indentifying indexes (0 or more). Note that the collection of coordinates/coordinate references for a PricingStructurePoint must not define a given dimension (other than "generic") more than once. This is to avoid ambiguity.

nodes.name: IdentifiedDate
nodes.documentation: A date which can be referenced elsewhere.

nodes.name: TradeNotionalChange
nodes.documentation: A structure describing a change to the trade notional.

nodes.name: PendingPayment
nodes.documentation: A structure representing a pending dividend or coupon payment.

nodes.name: RequestAllocationRetracted
nodes.documentation: A message withdrawing a request that a trade be split among several accounts.

nodes.name: DisruptionFallbacksEnum
nodes.documentation: The specification of how disruption fallbacks will be represented.

nodes.name: AccountType
nodes.documentation: The data type used for account type.

nodes.name: OptionStrike
nodes.documentation: A type for defining the strike price for an equity option. The strike price is either: (i) in respect of an index option transaction, the level of the relevant index specified or otherwise determined in the transaction; or (ii) in respect of a share option transaction, the price per share specified or otherwise determined in the transaction. This can be expressed either as a percentage of notional amount or as an absolute value.

nodes.name: CommodityQuantityFrequency
nodes.documentation: A type for defining the frequency at which the Notional Quantity is deemed to apply for purposes of calculating the Total Notional Quantity.

nodes.name: ParametricAdjustment
nodes.documentation: An adjustment used to accommodate a parameter of the input trade, e.g. the strike.

nodes.name: InterestCalculationTypeEnum
nodes.documentation: The type of calculation.

nodes.name: roundingDirection
nodes.documentation: The method of rounding a fractional number.

nodes.name: FinancialSwapLeg
nodes.documentation: The common components of a financially settled leg of a Commodity Swap. This is an abstract type and should be extended by commodity-specific types.

nodes.name: ValuationSetDetail
nodes.documentation: The amount of detail provided in the valuation set, e.g. is market environment data provided, are risk definitions provided, etc.

nodes.name: maximumInclusive
nodes.documentation: A type defining a number specified as positive decimal greater than 0 exclusive.

nodes.name: Strategy
nodes.documentation: A type defining a group of products making up a single trade.

nodes.name: AdjustableDatesOrRelativeDateOffset
nodes.documentation: A type for defining a series of dates, either as a list of adjustable dates, or a as a repeating sequence from a base date

nodes.name: Empty
nodes.documentation: A special type meant to be used for elements with no content and no attributes.

nodes.name: RelevantUnderlyingDateReference
nodes.documentation: Reference to relevant underlying date.

nodes.name: TouchConditionEnum
nodes.documentation: The specification of, for American-style digitals, whether the trigger level must be touched or not touched.

nodes.name: PremiumQuoteBasisEnum
nodes.documentation: The specification of how the premium for an FX OTC option is quoted.

nodes.name: spotPrice
nodes.documentation: A type defining a number specified as non negative decimal greater than 0 inclusive.

nodes.name: Trade
nodes.documentation: A type defining an FpML trade.

nodes.name: Rounding
nodes.documentation: A type defining a rounding direction and precision to be used in the rounding of a rate.

nodes.name: PortfolioConstituentReference
nodes.documentation: A structure used to group together individual messages that can be acted on at a group level.

nodes.name: EventStatusResponse
nodes.documentation: A type defining the content model for a message normally generated in response to a requestEventStatus request.

nodes.name: CutName
nodes.documentation: Allows for an expiryDateTime cut to be described by name.

nodes.name: DerivativeCalculationProcedure
nodes.documentation: A description of how a numerical derivative is computed.

nodes.name: Clearing
nodes.documentation: A structure describing a trade registration event that is part of a clearing process.

nodes.name: averagingMethod
nodes.documentation: The method of calculation to be used when averaging rates. Per ISDA 2000 Definitions, Section 6.2. Certain Definitions Relating to Floating Amounts.

nodes.name: DateRelativeToCalculationPeriodDates
nodes.documentation: A type to provide the ability to point to multiple payment nodes in the document through the unbounded paymentDatesReference.

nodes.name: FxSwapLeg
nodes.documentation: A type defining the details for one of the transactions in an FX swap.

nodes.name: TermPoint
nodes.documentation: A value point that can have a time dimension. Allows bid, mid, ask, and spread values to be represented.

nodes.name: ExerciseStyleEnum
nodes.documentation: The specification of how an OTC option will be exercised.

nodes.name: StubValue
nodes.documentation: A type defining how a stub calculation period amount is calculated and the start and end date of the stub. A single floating rate tenor different to that used for the regular part of the calculation periods schedule may be specified, or two floating rate tenors many be specified. If two floating rate tenors are specified then Linear Interpolation (in accordance with the 2000 ISDA Definitions, Section 8.3 Interpolation) is assumed to apply. Alternatively, an actual known stub rate or stub amount may be specified.

nodes.name: ExecutionVenueType
nodes.documentation: A type used to represent the type of market where a trade can be executed.

nodes.name: TradeDifference
nodes.documentation: A type used to record the details of a difference between two business objects/

nodes.name: stubPeriodType
nodes.documentation: Element to define how to deal with a none standard calculation period within a swap stream.

nodes.name: EquityForward
nodes.documentation: A type for defining equity forwards.

nodes.name: OilProductType
nodes.documentation: The type of physical commodity product to be delivered.

nodes.name: CapFloor
nodes.documentation: A type defining an interest rate cap, floor, or cap/floor strategy (e.g. collar) product.

nodes.name: Currency
nodes.documentation: The code representation of a currency or fund. By default it is a valid currency code as defined by the ISO standard 4217 - Codes for representation of currencies and funds http://www.iso.org/iso/en/prods-services/popstds/currencycodeslist.html.

nodes.name: ExceptionMessageHeader
nodes.documentation: A type defining the content model for an exception message header.

nodes.name: ReturnSwapBase
nodes.documentation: A type describing return swaps including return swaps (long form), total return swaps, and variance swaps.

nodes.name: Product
nodes.documentation: The base type which all FpML products extend.

nodes.name: GenericProduct
nodes.documentation: Simple product representation providing key information about a variety of different products. Generic products - for use in Transparency reporting to define a product that represents an OTC derivative transaction whose economics are not fully described using an FpML schema. In other views, generic products are present for convenience to support internal messaging and workflows that are cross-product. Generic products are not full trade representations as such they are not intended to be used for confirming trades.

nodes.name: CommodityAmericanExercise
nodes.documentation: A type for defining exercise procedures associated with an American style exercise of a commodity option.

nodes.name: ProductReference
nodes.documentation: Reference to a full FpML product.

nodes.name: InformationSource
nodes.documentation: A type defining the source for a piece of information (e.g. a rate refix or an fx fixing).

nodes.name: OptionBaseExtended
nodes.documentation: A complex type to support the credit default swap option.

nodes.name: CommodityForwardLeg
nodes.documentation: Physically settled leg of a physically settled Bullion Transaction.

nodes.name: UnitQuantity
nodes.documentation: A quantity and associated unit.

nodes.name: ShareExtraordinaryEventEnum
nodes.documentation: Defines the consequences of extraordinary events relating to the underlying.

nodes.name: OptionNumericStrike
nodes.documentation: A type for defining the strike price for an option as a numeric value without currency.

nodes.name: GenericDimension
nodes.documentation: A generic (user defined) dimension, e.g. for use in a correlation surface. e.g. a currency, stock, etc. This would take values like USD, GBP, JPY, or IBM, MSFT, etc.

nodes.name: RateTreatmentEnum
nodes.documentation: The specification of methods for converting rates from one basis to another.

nodes.name: SettlementPeriodsFixedPrice
nodes.documentation: A type defining the Fixed Price applicable to a range or ranges of Settlement Periods.

nodes.name: WeatherIndex
nodes.documentation: A type defining the Weather Index Level or Weather Index Strike Level.

nodes.name: CountryCode
nodes.documentation: The code representation of a country or an area of special sovereignty. By default it is a valid 2 character country code as defined by the ISO standard 3166-1 alpha-2 - Codes for representation of countries http://www.niso.org/standards/resources/3166.html.

nodes.name: VarianceSwap
nodes.documentation: A Variance Swap.

nodes.name: CalculationPeriodDates
nodes.documentation: A type defining the parameters used to generate the calculation period dates schedule, including the specification of any initial or final stub calculation periods. A calculation perod schedule consists of an optional initial stub calculation period, one or more regular calculation periods and an optional final stub calculation period. In the absence of any initial or final stub calculation periods, the regular part of the calculation period schedule is assumed to be between the effective date and the termination date. No implicit stubs are allowed, i.e. stubs must be explicitly specified using an appropriate combination of firstPeriodStateDate, firstRegularPeriodStartDate and lastRegularPeriodEndDate.

nodes.name: Account
nodes.documentation: A generic account that represents any party's account at another party. Parties may be identified by the account at another party.

nodes.name: DividendPeriodDividend
nodes.documentation: A time bounded dividend period, with an expected dividend for each period.

nodes.name: AveragingObservationList
nodes.documentation: An un ordered list of weighted averaging observations.

nodes.name: IndependentAmountConventionEnum
nodes.documentation: The type of independent amount convention.

nodes.name: SensitivitySetDefinitionReference
nodes.documentation: A reference to a sensitivity set definition.

nodes.name: InterestRateStream
nodes.documentation: A type defining the components specifiying an interest rate stream, including both a parametric and cashflow representation for the stream of payments.

nodes.name: FxFixing
nodes.documentation: A type that specifies the source for and timing of a fixing of an exchange rate. This is used in the agreement of non-deliverable forward trades as well as various types of FX OTC options that require observations against a particular rate.

nodes.name: ReportId
nodes.documentation: A type that can be used to hold an identifier for a report instance.

nodes.name: PositiveSchedule
nodes.documentation: A type defining a currency amount or a currency amount schedule.

nodes.name: Approval
nodes.documentation: A specific approval state in the workflow.

nodes.name: QueryParameter
nodes.documentation: A type representing criteria for defining a query portfolio. The criteria are made up of a QueryParameterId, QueryParameterValue and QueryParameterOperator.

nodes.name: QueryParameterValue
nodes.documentation: A type representing a value corresponding to an identifier for a parameter describing a query portfolio.

nodes.name: breakFeeElection
nodes.documentation: Defines the fee type.

nodes.name: CommodityOption
nodes.documentation: Commodity Option.

nodes.name: HTTPAttachmentReference
nodes.documentation: A special type that allows references to HTTP attachments identified with an HTTP "Content-ID" header, as is done with SOAP with Attachments (http://www.w3.org/TR/SOAP-attachments). Unlike with a normal FpML @href, the type is not IDREF, as the target is not identified by an XML @id attribute.

nodes.name: ReferencePoolItem
nodes.documentation: This type contains all the constituent weight and reference information.

nodes.name: MandatoryEarlyTerminationAdjustedDates
nodes.documentation: A type defining the adjusted dates associated with a mandatory early termination provision.

nodes.name: ExchangeTradedFund
nodes.documentation: An exchange traded fund whose price depends on exchange traded constituents.

nodes.name: DateTimeList
nodes.documentation: List of DateTimes

nodes.name: MetalPhysicalLeg
nodes.documentation: Physically settled leg of a physically settled Metal transaction.

nodes.name: dividendAmount
nodes.documentation: Refers to one on the 3 Amounts

nodes.name: ExerciseEvent
nodes.documentation: A type defining the adjusted dates associated with a particular exercise event.

nodes.name: FxAverageRateObservation
nodes.documentation: A type that, for average rate options, is used to describe each specific observation date, as opposed to a parametric frequency of rate observations.

nodes.name: EarlyTerminationProvision
nodes.documentation: A type defining an early termination provision for a swap. This early termination is at fair value, i.e. on termination the fair value of the product must be settled between the parties.

nodes.name: EntityName
nodes.documentation: The name of the reference entity. A free format string. FpML does not define usage rules for this element.

nodes.name: Reason
nodes.documentation: A type defining a content model for describing the nature and possible location of a error within a previous message.

nodes.name: ExchangeTradedContract
nodes.documentation: An exchange traded derivative contract.

nodes.name: PeriodEnum
nodes.documentation: The specification of a time period

nodes.name: ExercisePeriod
nodes.documentation: This defines the time interval to the start of the exercise period, i.e. the earliest exercise date, and the frequency of subsequent exercise dates (if any).

nodes.name: CoalTransportationEquipment
nodes.documentation: A scheme identifying the methods by which coal may be transported.

nodes.name: EventStatusItem
nodes.documentation: A type used in event status enquiry messages which relates an event identifier to its current status value.

nodes.name: ClassifiedPayment
nodes.documentation: A classified non negative payment.

nodes.name: StubPeriodTypeEnum
nodes.documentation: Element to define how to deal with a none standard calculation period within a swap stream.

nodes.name: SettlementPeriodDurationEnum
nodes.documentation: Defines the Settlement Period Duration for an Electricity Transaction.

nodes.name: NonDeliverableSettlement
nodes.documentation: A type defining the parameters used when the reference currency of the swapStream is non-deliverable.

nodes.name: LimitedCreditDefaultSwap
nodes.documentation: A limited version of the CDS type used as an underlyer to CDS options in Transparency view, to avoid requiring product type etc.

nodes.name: VolatilityMatrix
nodes.documentation: A matrix of volatilities with dimension 0-3.

nodes.name: Valuations
nodes.documentation: A set of valuation.

nodes.name: CancelableProvision
nodes.documentation: A type defining the right of a party to cancel a swap transaction on the specified exercise dates. The provision is for 'walkaway' cancellation (i.e. the fair value of the swap is not paid). A fee payable on exercise can be specified.

nodes.name: BasicQuotation
nodes.documentation: Some kind of numerical measure about an asset, eg. its NPV, together with characteristics of that measure.

nodes.name: MessageId
nodes.documentation: The data type use for message identifiers.

nodes.name: OptionExpiry
