nodes.documentation: A structure describing an option expiring (i.e. passing its last exercise time and becoming worthless.)

nodes.name: CoalStandardQuality
nodes.documentation: The quality attributes of the coal to be delivered.

nodes.name: CommodityDeliveryPeriods
nodes.documentation: The different options for specifying the Delivery Periods of a physical leg.

nodes.name: CommoditySettlementPeriodsNotionalQuantity
nodes.documentation: The notional quantity of electricity that applies to one or more groups of Settlement Periods.

nodes.name: StrategyFeature
nodes.documentation: A type for definining equity option simple strike or calendar spread strategy features.

nodes.name: CreditCurve
nodes.documentation: A generic credit curve definition.

nodes.name: TradeTimestamp
nodes.documentation: A generic trade timestamp

nodes.name: ElectricityPhysicalLeg
nodes.documentation: Physically settled leg of a physically settled electricity transaction.

nodes.name: MasterAgreement
nodes.documentation: An entity for defining the agreement executed between the parties and intended to govern all OTC derivatives transactions between those parties.

nodes.name: Commodity
nodes.documentation: A type describing a commodity underlying asset.

nodes.name: interestShortfallCap
nodes.documentation: The specification of the interest shortfall cap, applicable to mortgage derivatives.

nodes.name: DirectionalLegUnderlyerValuation
nodes.documentation: A type describing return which is driven by a Variance Calculation.

nodes.name: InflationRateCalculation
nodes.documentation: A type defining the components specifiying an Inflation Rate Calculation

nodes.name: SwapCurveValuation
nodes.documentation: A complex type to specify the amount to be paid by the buyer of the option if the option is exercised prior to the Early Call Date (Typically applicable to the convertible bond options).

nodes.name: ConsentGranted
nodes.documentation: A message indicating that the sender grants consent for the recipient to perform the requested action.

nodes.name: NonNegativeDecimal
nodes.documentation: A type defining a number specified as non negative decimal greater than 0 inclusive.

nodes.name: StreetAddress
nodes.documentation: A type that describes the set of street and building number information that identifies a postal address within a city.

nodes.name: ResourceType
nodes.documentation: The data type used for describing the type or purpose of a resource, e.g. "Confirmation".

nodes.name: CoalAttributeDecimal
nodes.documentation: The different options for specifying the attributes of a coal quality measure as a decimal value.

nodes.name: AllocationRefused
nodes.documentation: A message indicating that a request to allocate a trade has been refused by the sender.

nodes.name: DividendAmountTypeEnum
nodes.documentation: Refers to one on the 3 Amounts

nodes.name: rollConvention
nodes.documentation: The convention for determining the sequence of calculation period end dates. It is used in conjunction with a specified frequency and the regular period start date of a calculation period, e.g. semi-annual IMM roll dates.

nodes.name: RequestMessage
nodes.documentation: A type defining the content model for a request message that can be subsequently corrected or retracted.

nodes.name: ScheduledDates
nodes.documentation: A list of dates (cash flows, resets, etc.) that are relevant for this structure, e.g. next cash flow, last reset, etc. Provides a way to list upcoming or recent servicing dates related to this trade stream in a way that is simpler and more flexible than the FpML "cashflows" structure.

nodes.name: RelativeDateSequence
nodes.documentation: A type describing a date when this date is defined in reference to another date through one or several date offsets.

nodes.name: OrganizationCharacteristic
nodes.documentation: A characteristic of an organization used in declaring an end-user exception.

nodes.name: TradeChangeAdviceRetracted
nodes.documentation: Defines the structure for a message retracting a prior change advice.

nodes.name: EnvironmentalTrackingSystem
nodes.documentation: For US Emissions Allowance Transactions. A system where all electronic certificates are stored and emissions are tracked.

nodes.name: ExerciseProcedureOption
nodes.documentation: A type describing how notice of exercise should be given. This can be either manual or automatic.

nodes.name: ReasonCode
nodes.documentation: Defines a list of machine interpretable error codes.

nodes.name: FxSwap
nodes.documentation: A type defining either a spot/forward or forward/forward FX swap transaction.

nodes.name: MakeWholeAmount
nodes.documentation: A complex type to specify the amount to be paid by the buyer of the option if the option is exercised prior to the Early Call Date (Typically applicable to the convertible bond options).

nodes.name: SettlementPeriodsReference
nodes.documentation: Allows a set of Settlement Periods to reference one already defined elsewhere in the trade.

nodes.name: FPVFinalPriceElectionFallbackEnum
nodes.documentation: Specifies the fallback provisions in respect to the applicable Futures Price Valuation.

nodes.name: QuotedCurrencyPair
nodes.documentation: A type that describes the composition of a rate that has been quoted or is to be quoted. This includes the two currencies and the quotation relationship between the two currencies and is used as a building block throughout the FX specification.

nodes.name: Quotation
nodes.documentation: Some kind of numerical measure about an asset, eg. its NPV, together with characteristics of that measure, together with optional sensitivities.

nodes.name: QuotationCharacteristics
nodes.documentation: A type representing a set of characteristics that describe a quotation.

nodes.name: PerturbationType
nodes.documentation: The type of perturbation applied to compute a derivative perturbatively.

nodes.name: multiplier
nodes.documentation: A type defining a number specified as positive decimal greater than 0 exclusive.

nodes.name: OilDelivery
nodes.documentation: The physical delivery conditions for an oil product.

nodes.name: InterpolationMethod
nodes.documentation: The type of interpolation used.
